{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01Kbe5kPtMhnLj4RwZC3FsSh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GbsdsBtVvrEvPLb9NuaZzV","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24306,"cache_read_input_tokens":14955,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":24306,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUnpJzSHuhmadkgcFGRrK6","session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"f46a814d-dbec-4d8e-b19d-968137772e99"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GbsdsBtVvrEvPLb9NuaZzV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Edge Selection, Fanout, and Collect\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-02-20\n     4→**Status:** Approved\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→The current engine maps step outcomes to edges using only exit codes: exit 0\n     9→maps to the first declared result, non-zero maps to `\"fail\"`. This limits steps\n    10→to two possible edges and provides no mechanism for a step to select from\n    11→multiple named edges at runtime. The engine also executes steps sequentially\n    12→with no support for parallel branches.\n    13→\n    14→## Design\n    15→\n    16→### Result Protocol\n    17→\n    18→Steps communicate their chosen edge via a stdout marker:\n    19→\n    20→```\n    21→CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n    22→```\n    23→\n    24→The adapter scans captured stdout for the **last** line matching this prefix.\n    25→The marker line is stripped from the output written to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`.\n    26→\n    27→**Fallback (convention mode):** If no marker is found, the exit code determines\n    28→the result:\n    29→- Exit 0 → `\"success\"`\n    30→- Non-zero → `\"fail\"`\n    31→\n    32→The marker always takes precedence over exit code. A step that emits\n    33→`CLOCHE_RESULT:needs_research` but exits non-zero will route to `needs_research`,\n    34→not `fail`.\n    35→\n    36→**Undeclared or unwired results abort the workflow.** If a step produces a result\n    37→that is not in its declared `results` list, or that has no matching wire or\n    38→collect condition, the engine treats it as a fatal error and aborts the run.\n    39→There is no silent fallback.\n    40→\n    41→### Step Result Declarations\n    42→\n    43→Steps declare whatever results they need. There are no mandatory results.\n    44→\n    45→```\n    46→# Convention mode — exit code handles everything\n    47→step test {\n    48→    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n    49→    results = [success, fail]\n    50→}\n    51→\n    52→# Custom edges — LLM must emit marker for non-standard results\n    53→step analyze {\n    54→    prompt = file(\"prompts/analyze.md\")\n    55→    results = [success, fail, needs_research]\n    56→}\n    57→\n    58→# No standard edges — always requires explicit marker\n    59→step triage {\n    60→    prompt = file(\"prompts/triage.md\")\n    61→    results = [bug_fix, feature_request, needs_clarification]\n    62→}\n    63→```\n    64→\n    65→For `triage`: if the LLM exits 0 without a marker, the engine resolves\n    66→`\"success\"`, finds it not declared, and aborts. This forces the step to be\n    67→explicit.\n    68→\n    69→### Fanout\n    70→\n    71→Multiple wires from the same `(step, result)` pair trigger parallel execution:\n    72→\n    73→```\n    74→code:success -> test\n    75→code:success -> lint\n    76→```\n    77→\n    78→When `code` reports `success`, both `test` and `lint` start concurrently.\n    79→There is no implicit ordering between parallel branches.\n    80→\n    81→### Collect\n    82→\n    83→A `collect` keyword in the wiring section joins parallel branches:\n    84→\n    85→```\n    86→collect all(test:success, lint:success) -> merge\n    87→collect any(test:success, lint:success) -> quick_check\n    88→```\n    89→\n    90→- `all`: target step starts when every listed condition is satisfied.\n    91→- `any`: target step starts when any one condition is satisfied.\n    92→\n    93→**Unsatisfied collects:** If a collected step reports a result that doesn't\n    94→match its condition (e.g. `test` reports `fail` instead of `success`), that\n    95→condition is never satisfied. If the collect can never be fully satisfied, it\n    96→simply never fires. The run continues along whatever branches are still active.\n    97→\n    98→**`collect any` does not cancel other branches.** All parallel branches run to\n    99→completion. A future `collect any cancel(...)` variant could add cancellation\n   100→semantics.\n   101→\n   102→**Fanout and collect compose naturally:**\n   103→\n   104→```\n   105→code:success -> test\n   106→code:success -> lint\n   107→\n   108→collect all(test:success, lint:success) -> merge\n   109→test:fail -> fix\n   110→lint:fail -> fix\n   111→\n   112→merge:success -> done\n   113→```\n   114→\n   115→### DSL Grammar Extension\n   116→\n   117→```\n   118→wiring_entry  = simple_wire | collect_wire\n   119→simple_wire   = ident \":\" ident \"->\" ident\n   120→collect_wire  = \"collect\" collect_mode \"(\" condition_list \")\" \"->\" ident\n   121→collect_mode  = \"all\" | \"any\"\n   122→condition_list = condition (\",\" condition)*\n   123→condition     = ident \":\" ident\n   124→```\n   125→\n   126→### Domain Model Changes\n   127→\n   128→```go\n   129→type Wire struct {\n   130→    From   string\n   131→    Result string\n   132→    To     string\n   133→}\n   134→\n   135→type Collect struct {\n   136→    Mode       CollectMode\n   137→    Conditions []WireCondition\n   138→    To         string\n   139→}\n   140→\n   141→type CollectMode string\n   142→\n   143→const (\n   144→    CollectAll CollectMode = \"all\"\n   145→    CollectAny CollectMode = \"any\"\n   146→)\n   147→\n   148→type WireCondition struct {\n   149→    Step   string\n   150→    Result string\n   151→}\n   152→\n   153→type Workflow struct {\n   154→    Name      string\n   155→    Steps     map[string]*Step\n   156→    Wiring    []Wire\n   157→    Collects  []Collect\n   158→    EntryStep string\n   159→}\n   160→```\n   161→\n   162→`NextStep(name, result) (string, error)` is replaced by\n   163→`NextSteps(name, result) ([]string, error)` returning all wire targets for\n   164→the given pair.\n   165→\n   166→### Engine Rewrite\n   167→\n   168→The engine changes from a linear loop to a concurrent DAG walker.\n   169→\n   170→**State:**\n   171→\n   172→```go\n   173→type engineState struct {\n   174→    active    map[string]context.CancelFunc  // currently running steps\n   175→    pending   map[string]*collectState       // collects waiting for conditions\n   176→    completed map[string]string              // step name -> result\n   177→}\n   178→\n   179→type collectState struct {\n   180→    collect   *domain.Collect\n   181→    satisfied map[int]bool  // which conditions have been met\n   182→}\n   183→```\n   184→\n   185→**Execution cycle:**\n   186→\n   187→1. Start with `EntryStep`.\n   188→2. When a step completes with a result:\n   189→   - Record in `completed`.\n   190→   - Look up simple wires via `NextSteps` → launch targets concurrently.\n   191→   - Check all pending collects → mark satisfied conditions, fire any that\n   192→     are fully met.\n   193→3. Terminate when no steps are active and no collects can still fire.\n   194→\n   195→**Concurrency:** Each step runs in its own goroutine. A shared mutex protects\n   196→engine state. Step completion is communicated via a channel.\n   197→\n   198→**Termination:** The run succeeds if all branches reach `done`. It fails if any\n   199→branch reaches `abort` or any step execution errors. Dead branches from\n   200→unsatisfied collects are not an error — the run outcome depends on the\n   201→branches that did complete.\n   202→\n   203→**Max steps** is a total across all branches.\n   204→\n   205→### Adapter Changes\n   206→\n   207→**Shared result extraction** in `internal/protocol/result.go`:\n   208→\n   209→```go\n   210→func ExtractResult(output []byte) (result string, cleanOutput []byte, found bool)\n   211→```\n   212→\n   213→Scans for the last `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line, returns the result name and the\n   214→output with marker lines removed.\n   215→\n   216→**Generic adapter:** Captures stdout via `bufio.Scanner` on a pipe instead of\n   217→`CombinedOutput()`. Calls `ExtractResult`. Falls back to exit code convention.\n   218→\n   219→**Prompt adapter:** Appends result selection instructions to the assembled\n   220→prompt, listing all declared results:\n   221→\n   222→```\n   223→When you are finished, output exactly one of the following on its own line:\n   224→CLOCHE_RESULT:success\n   225→CLOCHE_RESULT:fail\n   226→CLOCHE_RESULT:needs_research\n   227→```\n   228→\n   229→After the LLM exits, scans output with `ExtractResult`. Same fallback.\n   230→\n   231→**`resultOrDefault` is removed.** Adapters return exactly one of: the marker\n   232→value, `\"success\"`, or `\"fail\"`. The engine validates against declared results\n   233→and wiring.\n   234→\n   235→### Validation\n   236→\n   237→Parse-time validation expands:\n   238→\n   239→- Every declared result must be wired (simple wire or collect condition).\n   240→- Every result referenced in a wire or collect must be declared by its step.\n   241→- Collect target steps must exist.\n   242→- Collect conditions must reference existing steps.\n   243→- Standard reachability checks still apply.\n   244→\n   245→### Backward Compatibility\n   246→\n   247→Existing workflows using `pass`/`fail` must rename `pass` to `success` and\n   248→update their wiring accordingly. This is the only breaking change.\n   249→\n   250→Workflows that only use `success` and `fail` results continue to work via\n   251→exit-code convention with no stdout markers needed. `collect` is purely\n   252→additive syntax — workflows without it parse and run identically.\n   253→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUnpJzSHuhmadkgcFGRrK6","session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"6a591962-0c44-4e49-98a2-d8fac0bbfc0c"}
