{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QQo8qiKqC3FvNan12C4FNH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package main\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"context\"\n     5→\t\"fmt\"\n     6→\t\"os\"\n     7→\t\"os/signal\"\n     8→\t\"syscall\"\n     9→\n    10→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/agent\"\n    11→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/version\"\n    12→)\n    13→\n    14→func main() {\n    15→\tif len(os.Args) >= 2 && (os.Args[1] == \"-v\" || os.Args[1] == \"--version\") {\n    16→\t\tfmt.Printf(\"cloche-agent %s\\n\", version.Version())\n    17→\t\treturn\n    18→\t}\n    19→\n    20→\tif len(os.Args) < 2 {\n    21→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche-agent <workflow-file> [--resume-from <step>]\\n\")\n    22→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n    23→\t}\n    24→\n    25→\tworkflowPath := os.Args[1]\n    26→\tworkDir, _ := os.Getwd()\n    27→\n    28→\t// Parse --resume-from flag\n    29→\tvar resumeFromStep string\n    30→\tfor i := 2; i < len(os.Args); i++ {\n    31→\t\tif os.Args[i] == \"--resume-from\" && i+1 < len(os.Args) {\n    32→\t\t\ti++\n    33→\t\t\tresumeFromStep = os.Args[i]\n    34→\t\t}\n    35→\t}\n    36→\n    37→\tctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n    38→\tdefer cancel()\n    39→\n    40→\tsigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n    41→\tsignal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n    42→\tgo func() {\n    43→\t\t<-sigCh\n    44→\t\tcancel()\n    45→\t}()\n    46→\n    47→\trunID := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_RUN_ID\")\n    48→\tos.Unsetenv(\"CLOCHE_RUN_ID\")\n    49→\n    50→\trunner := agent.NewRunner(agent.RunnerConfig{\n    51→\t\tWorkflowPath:   workflowPath,\n    52→\t\tWorkDir:        workDir,\n    53→\t\tStatusOutput:   os.Stdout,\n    54→\t\tRunID:          runID,\n    55→\t\tResumeFromStep: resumeFromStep,\n    56→\t})\n    57→\n    58→\tif err := runner.Run(ctx); err != nil {\n    59→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n    60→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n    61→\t}\n    62→}\n    63→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JBcSznxqHEKxbG5yXzGdkP","session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"039c802c-391c-47c2-bcda-004e0eca8929"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VJ1jCx7mpS73vogWdkm9Gg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Edge Selection, Fanout, and Collect — Implementation Plan\n     2→\n     3→> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n     4→\n     5→**Goal:** Replace the exit-code-only result mechanism with a stdout-marker protocol, add fanout (parallel branches) and collect (join) to the workflow engine.\n     6→\n     7→**Architecture:** Bottom-up: domain types → result extraction → DSL parsing → validation → adapters → engine rewrite → runner/example updates. Each layer is testable in isolation before the next builds on it.\n     8→\n     9→**Tech Stack:** Go, testify, `bufio` for stdout scanning.\n    10→\n    11→**Design doc:** `docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md`\n    12→\n    13→---\n    14→\n    15→### Task 1: Add domain types for Collect\n    16→\n    17→**Files:**\n    18→- Modify: `internal/domain/workflow.go`\n    19→\n    20→**Step 1: Add Collect types after the existing Wire type**\n    21→\n    22→After the `Wire` struct (line 27), add:\n    23→\n    24→```go\n    25→type CollectMode string\n    26→\n    27→const (\n    28→\tCollectAll CollectMode = \"all\"\n    29→\tCollectAny CollectMode = \"any\"\n    30→)\n    31→\n    32→type WireCondition struct {\n    33→\tStep   string\n    34→\tResult string\n    35→}\n    36→\n    37→type Collect struct {\n    38→\tMode       CollectMode\n    39→\tConditions []WireCondition\n    40→\tTo         string\n    41→}\n    42→```\n    43→\n    44→**Step 2: Add `Collects` field to `Workflow` struct**\n    45→\n    46→Add `Collects []Collect` after the `Wiring` field in the `Workflow` struct.\n    47→\n    48→**Step 3: Verify it compiles**\n    49→\n    50→Run: `go build ./internal/domain/...`\n    51→Expected: success, no errors.\n    52→\n    53→**Step 4: Commit**\n    54→\n    55→```bash\n    56→git add internal/domain/workflow.go\n    57→git commit -m \"feat(domain): add Collect, CollectMode, WireCondition types\"\n    58→```\n    59→\n    60→---\n    61→\n    62→### Task 2: Replace NextStep with NextSteps\n    63→\n    64→**Files:**\n    65→- Modify: `internal/domain/workflow.go`\n    66→- Modify: `internal/domain/workflow_test.go`\n    67→\n    68→**Step 1: Write failing tests for NextSteps**\n    69→\n    70→Replace the existing `TestWorkflow_NextStep` test and add a fanout test in `workflow_test.go`:\n    71→\n    72→```go\n    73→func TestWorkflow_NextSteps(t *testing.T) {\n    74→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n    75→\t\tName: \"test-workflow\",\n    76→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n    77→\t\t\t\"code\":  {Name: \"code\", Type: domain.StepTypeAgent, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n    78→\t\t\t\"check\": {Name: \"check\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"pass\"}},\n    79→\t\t},\n    80→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n    81→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: \"check\"},\n    82→\t\t\t{From: \"check\", Result: \"pass\", To: domain.StepDone},\n    83→\t\t},\n    84→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n    85→\t}\n    86→\n    87→\tnext, err := wf.NextSteps(\"code\", \"success\")\n    88→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    89→\tassert.Equal(t, []string{\"check\"}, next)\n    90→\n    91→\tnext, err = wf.NextSteps(\"check\", \"pass\")\n    92→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    93→\tassert.Equal(t, []string{domain.StepDone}, next)\n    94→\n    95→\tnext, err = wf.NextSteps(\"code\", \"nonexistent\")\n    96→\tassert.Error(t, err)\n    97→\tassert.Nil(t, next)\n    98→}\n    99→\n   100→func TestWorkflow_NextSteps_Fanout(t *testing.T) {\n   101→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   102→\t\tName: \"fanout\",\n   103→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   104→\t\t\t\"code\": {Name: \"code\", Type: domain.StepTypeAgent, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   105→\t\t\t\"test\": {Name: \"test\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"pass\"}},\n   106→\t\t\t\"lint\": {Name: \"lint\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"pass\"}},\n   107→\t\t},\n   108→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   109→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: \"test\"},\n   110→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: \"lint\"},\n   111→\t\t\t{From: \"test\", Result: \"pass\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   112→\t\t\t{From: \"lint\", Result: \"pass\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   113→\t\t},\n   114→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n   115→\t}\n   116→\n   117→\tnext, err := wf.NextSteps(\"code\", \"success\")\n   118→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   119→\tassert.Equal(t, []string{\"test\", \"lint\"}, next)\n   120→}\n   121→```\n   122→\n   123→**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n   124→\n   125→Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -run TestWorkflow_NextSteps -v`\n   126→Expected: FAIL — `NextSteps` not defined.\n   127→\n   128→**Step 3: Implement NextSteps, keep NextStep as deprecated wrapper**\n   129→\n   130→In `workflow.go`, add `NextSteps` and update `NextStep`:\n   131→\n   132→```go\n   133→func (w *Workflow) NextSteps(stepName, result string) ([]string, error) {\n   134→\tvar targets []string\n   135→\tfor _, wire := range w.Wiring {\n   136→\t\tif wire.From == stepName && wire.Result == result {\n   137→\t\t\ttargets = append(targets, wire.To)\n   138→\t\t}\n   139→\t}\n   140→\tif len(targets) == 0 {\n   141→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"workflow %q: no wiring for step %q result %q\", w.Name, stepName, result)\n   142→\t}\n   143→\treturn targets, nil\n   144→}\n   145→\n   146→func (w *Workflow) NextStep(stepName, result string) (string, error) {\n   147→\ttargets, err := w.NextSteps(stepName, result)\n   148→\tif err != nil {\n   149→\t\treturn \"\", err\n   150→\t}\n   151→\treturn targets[0], nil\n   152→}\n   153→```\n   154→\n   155→**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n   156→\n   157→Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -v`\n   158→Expected: all PASS.\n   159→\n   160→**Step 5: Commit**\n   161→\n   162→```bash\n   163→git add internal/domain/workflow.go internal/domain/workflow_test.go\n   164→git commit -m \"feat(domain): add NextSteps for fanout, keep NextStep as wrapper\"\n   165→```\n   166→\n   167→---\n   168→\n   169→### Task 3: Add result extraction protocol\n   170→\n   171→**Files:**\n   172→- Create: `internal/protocol/result.go`\n   173→- Create: `internal/protocol/result_test.go`\n   174→\n   175→**Step 1: Write failing tests**\n   176→\n   177→Create `internal/protocol/result_test.go`:\n   178→\n   179→```go\n   180→package protocol_test\n   181→\n   182→import (\n   183→\t\"testing\"\n   184→\n   185→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n   186→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n   187→)\n   188→\n   189→func TestExtractResult_Found(t *testing.T) {\n   190→\toutput := []byte(\"some output\\nCLOCHE_RESULT:needs_research\\nmore output\\n\")\n   191→\tresult, clean, found := protocol.ExtractResult(output)\n   192→\tassert.True(t, found)\n   193→\tassert.Equal(t, \"needs_research\", result)\n   194→\tassert.NotContains(t, string(clean), \"CLOCHE_RESULT\")\n   195→\tassert.Contains(t, string(clean), \"some output\")\n   196→\tassert.Contains(t, string(clean), \"more output\")\n   197→}\n   198→\n   199→func TestExtractResult_LastWins(t *testing.T) {\n   200→\toutput := []byte(\"CLOCHE_RESULT:first\\nstuff\\nCLOCHE_RESULT:second\\n\")\n   201→\tresult, _, found := protocol.ExtractResult(output)\n   202→\tassert.True(t, found)\n   203→\tassert.Equal(t, \"second\", result)\n   204→}\n   205→\n   206→func TestExtractResult_NotFound(t *testing.T) {\n   207→\toutput := []byte(\"just normal output\\nexit 0\\n\")\n   208→\tresult, clean, found := protocol.ExtractResult(output)\n   209→\tassert.False(t, found)\n   210→\tassert.Empty(t, result)\n   211→\tassert.Equal(t, output, clean)\n   212→}\n   213→\n   214→func TestExtractResult_EmptyOutput(t *testing.T) {\n   215→\tresult, clean, found := protocol.ExtractResult([]byte{})\n   216→\tassert.False(t, found)\n   217→\tassert.Empty(t, result)\n   218→\tassert.Empty(t, clean)\n   219→}\n   220→\n   221→func TestExtractResult_MarkerOnly(t *testing.T) {\n   222→\toutput := []byte(\"CLOCHE_RESULT:success\\n\")\n   223→\tresult, clean, found := protocol.ExtractResult(output)\n   224→\tassert.True(t, found)\n   225→\tassert.Equal(t, \"success\", result)\n   226→\tassert.Empty(t, string(clean))\n   227→}\n   228→```\n   229→\n   230→**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n   231→\n   232→Run: `go test ./internal/protocol/ -run TestExtractResult -v`\n   233→Expected: FAIL — `ExtractResult` not defined.\n   234→\n   235→**Step 3: Implement ExtractResult**\n   236→\n   237→Create `internal/protocol/result.go`:\n   238→\n   239→```go\n   240→package protocol\n   241→\n   242→import (\n   243→\t\"bytes\"\n   244→\t\"strings\"\n   245→)\n   246→\n   247→const ResultPrefix = \"CLOCHE_RESULT:\"\n   248→\n   249→// ExtractResult scans output for the last CLOCHE_RESULT:<name> line.\n   250→// Returns the result name, the output with all marker lines removed, and\n   251→// whether a marker was found.\n   252→func ExtractResult(output []byte) (result string, cleanOutput []byte, found bool) {\n   253→\tvar clean [][]byte\n   254→\tfor _, line := range bytes.Split(output, []byte(\"\\n\")) {\n   255→\t\ttrimmed := strings.TrimSpace(string(line))\n   256→\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(trimmed, ResultPrefix) {\n   257→\t\t\tresult = trimmed[len(ResultPrefix):]\n   258→\t\t\tfound = true\n   259→\t\t} else {\n   260→\t\t\tclean = append(clean, line)\n   261→\t\t}\n   262→\t}\n   263→\t// Rejoin and trim trailing empty line from split\n   264→\tjoined := bytes.Join(clean, []byte(\"\\n\"))\n   265→\tjoined = bytes.TrimRight(joined, \"\\n\")\n   266→\tif len(joined) > 0 {\n   267→\t\tjoined = append(joined, '\\n')\n   268→\t}\n   269→\treturn result, joined, found\n   270→}\n   271→```\n   272→\n   273→**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n   274→\n   275→Run: `go test ./internal/protocol/ -run TestExtractResult -v`\n   276→Expected: all PASS.\n   277→\n   278→**Step 5: Commit**\n   279→\n   280→```bash\n   281→git add internal/protocol/result.go internal/protocol/result_test.go\n   282→git commit -m \"feat(protocol): add ExtractResult for CLOCHE_RESULT stdout marker\"\n   283→```\n   284→\n   285→---\n   286→\n   287→### Task 4: Update generic adapter to use result extraction\n   288→\n   289→**Files:**\n   290→- Modify: `internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`\n   291→- Modify: `internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic_test.go`\n   292→\n   293→**Step 1: Write failing tests for marker support**\n   294→\n   295→Add to `generic_test.go`:\n   296→\n   297→```go\n   298→func TestGenericAdapter_StdoutMarkerOverridesExitCode(t *testing.T) {\n   299→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n   300→\tadapter := generic.New()\n   301→\tstep := &domain.Step{\n   302→\t\tName:    \"analyze\",\n   303→\t\tType:    domain.StepTypeScript,\n   304→\t\tResults: []string{\"success\", \"fail\", \"needs_research\"},\n   305→\t\tConfig:  map[string]string{\"run\": \"echo 'analyzing...' && echo 'CLOCHE_RESULT:needs_research'\"},\n   306→\t}\n   307→\n   308→\tresult, err := adapter.Execute(context.Background(), step, dir)\n   309→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   310→\tassert.Equal(t, \"needs_research\", result)\n   311→\n   312→\t// Verify marker is stripped from log\n   313→\tlogPath := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"output\", \"analyze.log\")\n   314→\tcontent, err := os.ReadFile(logPath)\n   315→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   316→\tassert.NotContains(t, string(content), \"CLOCHE_RESULT\")\n   317→\tassert.Contains(t, string(content), \"analyzing...\")\n   318→}\n   319→\n   320→func TestGenericAdapter_MarkerOverridesFailExitCode(t *testing.T) {\n   321→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n   322→\tadapter := generic.New()\n   323→\tstep := &domain.Step{\n   324→\t\tName:    \"triage\",\n   325→\t\tType:    domain.StepTypeScript,\n   326→\t\tResults: []string{\"bug_fix\", \"feature_request\"},\n   327→\t\tConfig:  map[string]string{\"run\": \"echo 'CLOCHE_RESULT:bug_fix' && exit 1\"},\n   328→\t}\n   329→\n   330→\tresult, err := adapter.Execute(context.Background(), step, dir)\n   331→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   332→\tassert.Equal(t, \"bug_fix\", result)\n   333→}\n   334→```\n   335→\n   336→**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n   337→\n   338→Run: `go test ./internal/adapters/agents/generic/ -run TestGenericAdapter_StdoutMarker -v`\n   339→Expected: FAIL — returns \"success\" or \"fail\" instead of the marker value.\n   340→\n   341→**Step 3: Update generic adapter**\n   342→\n   343→Replace the `Execute` method in `generic.go`. Remove `resultOrDefault`. Use `protocol.ExtractResult`:\n   344→\n   345→```go\n   346→package generic\n   347→\n   348→import (\n   349→\t\"context\"\n   350→\t\"os\"\n   351→\t\"os/exec\"\n   352→\t\"path/filepath\"\n   353→\n   354→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n   355→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n   356→)\n   357→\n   358→type Adapter struct{}\n   359→\n   360→func New() *Adapter {\n   361→\treturn &Adapter{}\n   362→}\n   363→\n   364→func (a *Adapter) Name() string {\n   365→\treturn \"generic\"\n   366→}\n   367→\n   368→func (a *Adapter) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (string, error) {\n   369→\tcmdStr := step.Config[\"run\"]\n   370→\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"sh\", \"-c\", cmdStr)\n   371→\tcmd.Dir = workDir\n   372→\n   373→\toutput, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n   374→\n   375→\t// Extract result marker before writing logs\n   376→\tmarkerResult, cleanOutput, found := protocol.ExtractResult(output)\n   377→\n   378→\t// Write cleaned output to log file\n   379→\toutputDir := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\")\n   380→\tif mkErr := os.MkdirAll(outputDir, 0755); mkErr == nil {\n   381→\t\t_ = os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(outputDir, step.Name+\".log\"), cleanOutput, 0644)\n   382→\t}\n   383→\n   384→\tif err != nil {\n   385→\t\tif _, ok := err.(*exec.ExitError); ok {\n   386→\t\t\tif found {\n   387→\t\t\t\treturn markerResult, nil\n   388→\t\t\t}\n   389→\t\t\treturn \"fail\", nil\n   390→\t\t}\n   391→\t\treturn \"\", err\n   392→\t}\n   393→\n   394→\tif found {\n   395→\t\treturn markerResult, nil\n   396→\t}\n   397→\treturn \"success\", nil\n   398→}\n   399→```\n   400→\n   401→**Step 4: Run all generic adapter tests**\n   402→\n   403→Run: `go test ./internal/adapters/agents/generic/ -v`\n   404→Expected: all PASS. Existing tests may need result name updates (`\"pass\"` → `\"success\"`) since `resultOrDefault` is gone. Update the `TestGenericAdapter_CapturesOutput` and `TestGenericAdapter_CapturesOutputOnFailure` tests: change their `Results` to `[]string{\"success\", \"fail\"}` and expected results accordingly. The `TestGenericAdapter_CapturesOutput` test currently expects `\"pass\"` for exit 0 — it should now expect `\"success\"` (update the `Results` field from `[\"pass\", \"fail\"]` to `[\"success\", \"fail\"]`).\n   405→\n   406→**Step 5: Commit**\n   407→\n   408→```bash\n   409→git add internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic_test.go\n   410→git commit -m \"feat(generic): use ExtractResult protocol, remove resultOrDefault\"\n   411→```\n   412→\n   413→---\n   414→\n   415→### Task 5: Update prompt adapter to use result extraction\n   416→\n   417→**Files:**\n   418→- Modify: `internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`\n   419→- Modify: `internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt_test.go`\n   420→\n   421→**Step 1: Write failing test for result instruction injection**\n   422→\n   423→Add to `prompt_test.go`:\n   424→\n   425→```go\n   426→func TestPromptAdapter_InjectsResultInstructions(t *testing.T) {\n   427→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n   428→\n   429→\tadapter := &prompt.Adapter{\n   430→\t\tCommand: \"sh\",\n   431→\t\tArgs:    []string{\"-c\", \"cat > captured_prompt.txt\"},\n   432→\t}\n   433→\n   434→\tstep := &domain.Step{\n   435→\t\tName:    \"analyze\",\n   436→\t\tType:    domain.StepTypeAgent,\n   437→\t\tResults: []string{\"success\", \"fail\", \"needs_research\"},\n   438→\t\tConfig:  map[string]string{\"prompt\": \"Analyze the code.\"},\n   439→\t}\n   440→\n   441→\t_, err := adapter.Execute(context.Background(), step, dir)\n   442→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   443→\n   444→\tcaptured, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"captured_prompt.txt\"))\n   445→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   446→\tassert.Contains(t, string(captured), \"CLOCHE_RESULT:success\")\n   447→\tassert.Contains(t, string(captured), \"CLOCHE_RESULT:fail\")\n   448→\tassert.Contains(t, string(captured), \"CLOCHE_RESULT:needs_research\")\n   449→}\n   450→\n   451→func TestPromptAdapter_StdoutMarkerSelectsResult(t *testing.T) {\n   452→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n   453→\n   454→\tadapter := &prompt.Adapter{\n   455→\t\tCommand: \"sh\",\n   456→\t\tArgs:    []string{\"-c\", \"cat > /dev/null && echo 'CLOCHE_RESULT:needs_research'\"},\n   457→\t}\n   458→\n   459→\tstep := &domain.Step{\n   460→\t\tName:    \"analyze\",\n   461→\t\tType:    domain.StepTypeAgent,\n   462→\t\tResults: []string{\"success\", \"fail\", \"needs_research\"},\n   463→\t\tConfig:  map[string]string{\"prompt\": \"Analyze the code.\"},\n   464→\t}\n   465→\n   466→\tresult, err := adapter.Execute(context.Background(), step, dir)\n   467→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   468→\tassert.Equal(t, \"needs_research\", result)\n   469→}\n   470→```\n   471→\n   472→**Step 2: Run to verify they fail**\n   473→\n   474→Run: `go test ./internal/adapters/agents/prompt/ -run \"TestPromptAdapter_Injects|TestPromptAdapter_StdoutMarker\" -v`\n   475→Expected: FAIL.\n   476→\n   477→**Step 3: Update prompt adapter**\n   478→\n   479→Key changes to `prompt.go`:\n   480→1. `assemblePrompt` takes `step.Results` and appends result selection instructions.\n   481→2. After the command runs, capture stdout and use `protocol.ExtractResult`.\n   482→3. Remove `resultOrDefault`.\n   483→4. Fall back to exit-code convention if no marker found.\n   484→\n   485→The `Execute` method needs to capture stdout (currently it uses `cmd.Stdout = &stdout` but doesn't scan for markers). Add extraction after `cmd.Run()`.\n   486→\n   487→In `assemblePrompt`, append a new section:\n   488→\n   489→```go\n   490→// 4. Result selection instructions\n   491→if len(step.Results) > 0 {\n   492→\tvar resultLines []string\n   493→\tresultLines = append(resultLines, \"## Result Selection\")\n   494→\tresultLines = append(resultLines, \"When you are finished, output exactly one of the following on its own line:\")\n   495→\tfor _, r := range step.Results {\n   496→\t\tresultLines = append(resultLines, protocol.ResultPrefix+r)\n   497→\t}\n   498→\tparts = append(parts, strings.Join(resultLines, \"\\n\"))\n   499→}\n   500→```\n   501→\n   502→In `Execute`, after `cmd.Run()`:\n   503→\n   504→```go\n   505→markerResult, _, found := protocol.ExtractResult(stdout.Bytes())\n   506→\n   507→if err := cmd.Run(); err != nil {\n   508→\tif _, ok := err.(*exec.ExitError); ok {\n   509→\t\tif found {\n   510→\t\t\treturn markerResult, nil\n   511→\t\t}\n   512→\t\treturn \"fail\", nil\n   513→\t}\n   514→\treturn \"\", err\n   515→}\n   516→\n   517→if found {\n   518→\treturn markerResult, nil\n   519→}\n   520→return \"success\", nil\n   521→```\n   522→\n   523→**Step 4: Run all prompt adapter tests**\n   524→\n   525→Run: `go test ./internal/adapters/agents/prompt/ -v`\n   526→Expected: all PASS. Existing tests that expect `\"fixed\"` as first result via `resultOrDefault` need updating — `TestPromptAdapter_IncludesFeedback` expects `\"fixed\"` but will now get `\"success\"` (exit 0, no marker). Update that test's expected result to `\"success\"`, or have its mock emit the marker.\n   527→\n   528→**Step 5: Commit**\n   529→\n   530→```bash\n   531→git add internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt_test.go\n   532→git commit -m \"feat(prompt): inject result instructions, use ExtractResult protocol\"\n   533→```\n   534→\n   535→---\n   536→\n   537→### Task 6: Parse `collect` in DSL\n   538→\n   539→**Files:**\n   540→- Modify: `internal/dsl/parser.go`\n   541→- Modify: `internal/dsl/parser_test.go`\n   542→\n   543→**Step 1: Write failing test**\n   544→\n   545→Add to `parser_test.go`:\n   546→\n   547→```go\n   548→func TestParser_CollectAll(t *testing.T) {\n   549→\tinput := `workflow \"parallel\" {\n   550→  step code {\n   551→    prompt = \"write code\"\n   552→    results = [success]\n   553→  }\n   554→  step test {\n   555→    run = \"make test\"\n   556→    results = [success, fail]\n   557→  }\n   558→  step lint {\n   559→    run = \"make lint\"\n   560→    results = [success, fail]\n   561→  }\n   562→  step merge {\n   563→    run = \"echo merged\"\n   564→    results = [success]\n   565→  }\n   566→\n   567→  code:success -> test\n   568→  code:success -> lint\n   569→  test:fail -> abort\n   570→  lint:fail -> abort\n   571→  collect all(test:success, lint:success) -> merge\n   572→  merge:success -> done\n   573→}`\n   574→\n   575→\twf, err := dsl.Parse(input)\n   576→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   577→\n   578→\trequire.Len(t, wf.Collects, 1)\n   579→\tc := wf.Collects[0]\n   580→\tassert.Equal(t, domain.CollectAll, c.Mode)\n   581→\tassert.Equal(t, \"merge\", c.To)\n   582→\trequire.Len(t, c.Conditions, 2)\n   583→\tassert.Equal(t, \"test\", c.Conditions[0].Step)\n   584→\tassert.Equal(t, \"success\", c.Conditions[0].Result)\n   585→\tassert.Equal(t, \"lint\", c.Conditions[1].Step)\n   586→\tassert.Equal(t, \"success\", c.Conditions[1].Result)\n   587→}\n   588→\n   589→func TestParser_CollectAny(t *testing.T) {\n   590→\tinput := `workflow \"race\" {\n   591→  step fast {\n   592→    run = \"echo fast\"\n   593→    results = [success]\n   594→  }\n   595→  step slow {\n   596→    run = \"sleep 1 && echo slow\"\n   597→    results = [success]\n   598→  }\n   599→  step next {\n   600→    run = \"echo next\"\n   601→    results = [success]\n   602→  }\n   603→\n   604→  collect any(fast:success, slow:success) -> next\n   605→  next:success -> done\n   606→}`\n   607→\n   608→\twf, err := dsl.Parse(input)\n   609→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   610→\n   611→\trequire.Len(t, wf.Collects, 1)\n   612→\tassert.Equal(t, domain.CollectAny, wf.Collects[0].Mode)\n   613→}\n   614→```\n   615→\n   616→**Step 2: Run to verify they fail**\n   617→\n   618→Run: `go test ./internal/dsl/ -run \"TestParser_Collect\" -v`\n   619→Expected: FAIL — parser doesn't recognize `collect`.\n   620→\n   621→**Step 3: Implement collect parsing**\n   622→\n   623→In `parser.go`, update the `parseWorkflow` loop. When `p.current` is `TokenIdent` with literal `\"collect\"`, call a new `parseCollect` method:\n   624→\n   625→```go\n   626→// In the parseWorkflow loop, add a branch before the wire check:\n   627→} else if p.current.Type == TokenIdent && p.current.Literal == \"collect\" {\n   628→\tcollect, err := p.parseCollect()\n   629→\tif err != nil {\n   630→\t\treturn nil, err\n   631→\t}\n   632→\twf.Collects = append(wf.Collects, collect)\n   633→}\n   634→```\n   635→\n   636→Add the `parseCollect` method:\n   637→\n   638→```go\n   639→func (p *Parser) parseCollect() (domain.Collect, error) {\n   640→\tp.advance() // consume \"collect\"\n   641→\n   642→\tmodeTok, err := p.expect(TokenIdent)\n   643→\tif err != nil {\n   644→\t\treturn domain.Collect{}, fmt.Errorf(\"expected 'all' or 'any': %w\", err)\n   645→\t}\n   646→\n   647→\tvar mode domain.CollectMode\n   648→\tswitch modeTok.Literal {\n   649→\tcase \"all\":\n   650→\t\tmode = domain.CollectAll\n   651→\tcase \"any\":\n   652→\t\tmode = domain.CollectAny\n   653→\tdefault:\n   654→\t\treturn domain.Collect{}, fmt.Errorf(\"line %d col %d: expected 'all' or 'any', got %q\",\n   655→\t\t\tmodeTok.Line, modeTok.Col, modeTok.Literal)\n   656→\t}\n   657→\n   658→\tif _, err := p.expect(TokenLParen); err != nil {\n   659→\t\treturn domain.Collect{}, err\n   660→\t}\n   661→\n   662→\tvar conditions []domain.WireCondition\n   663→\tfor p.current.Type != TokenRParen && p.current.Type != TokenEOF {\n   664→\t\tstepTok, err := p.expect(TokenIdent)\n   665→\t\tif err != nil {\n   666→\t\t\treturn domain.Collect{}, fmt.Errorf(\"expected step name in collect: %w\", err)\n   667→\t\t}\n   668→\t\tif _, err := p.expect(TokenColon); err != nil {\n   669→\t\t\treturn domain.Collect{}, err\n   670→\t\t}\n   671→\t\tresultTok, err := p.expect(TokenIdent)\n   672→\t\tif err != nil {\n   673→\t\t\treturn domain.Collect{}, fmt.Errorf(\"expected result name in collect: %w\", err)\n   674→\t\t}\n   675→\t\tconditions = append(conditions, domain.WireCondition{Step: stepTok.Literal, Result: resultTok.Literal})\n   676→\t\tif p.current.Type == TokenComma {\n   677→\t\t\tp.advance()\n   678→\t\t}\n   679→\t}\n   680→\n   681→\tif _, err := p.expect(TokenRParen); err != nil {\n   682→\t\treturn domain.Collect{}, err\n   683→\t}\n   684→\tif _, err := p.expect(TokenArrow); err != nil {\n   685→\t\treturn domain.Collect{}, err\n   686→\t}\n   687→\n   688→\ttoTok, err := p.expect(TokenIdent)\n   689→\tif err != nil {\n   690→\t\treturn domain.Collect{}, fmt.Errorf(\"expected target step: %w\", err)\n   691→\t}\n   692→\n   693→\treturn domain.Collect{\n   694→\t\tMode:       mode,\n   695→\t\tConditions: conditions,\n   696→\t\tTo:         toTok.Literal,\n   697→\t}, nil\n   698→}\n   699→```\n   700→\n   701→**Step 4: Run tests**\n   702→\n   703→Run: `go test ./internal/dsl/ -v`\n   704→Expected: all PASS.\n   705→\n   706→**Step 5: Commit**\n   707→\n   708→```bash\n   709→git add internal/dsl/parser.go internal/dsl/parser_test.go\n   710→git commit -m \"feat(dsl): parse collect all/any wiring syntax\"\n   711→```\n   712→\n   713→---\n   714→\n   715→### Task 7: Update validation for collects\n   716→\n   717→**Files:**\n   718→- Modify: `internal/domain/workflow.go`\n   719→- Modify: `internal/domain/workflow_test.go`\n   720→\n   721→**Step 1: Write failing tests**\n   722→\n   723→Add to `workflow_test.go`:\n   724→\n   725→```go\n   726→func TestWorkflow_Validate_CollectValid(t *testing.T) {\n   727→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   728→\t\tName: \"parallel\",\n   729→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   730→\t\t\t\"code\":  {Name: \"code\", Type: domain.StepTypeAgent, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   731→\t\t\t\"test\":  {Name: \"test\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\", \"fail\"}},\n   732→\t\t\t\"lint\":  {Name: \"lint\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\", \"fail\"}},\n   733→\t\t\t\"merge\": {Name: \"merge\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   734→\t\t},\n   735→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   736→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: \"test\"},\n   737→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: \"lint\"},\n   738→\t\t\t{From: \"test\", Result: \"fail\", To: domain.StepAbort},\n   739→\t\t\t{From: \"lint\", Result: \"fail\", To: domain.StepAbort},\n   740→\t\t\t{From: \"merge\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   741→\t\t},\n   742→\t\tCollects: []domain.Collect{\n   743→\t\t\t{\n   744→\t\t\t\tMode: domain.CollectAll,\n   745→\t\t\t\tConditions: []domain.WireCondition{\n   746→\t\t\t\t\t{Step: \"test\", Result: \"success\"},\n   747→\t\t\t\t\t{Step: \"lint\", Result: \"success\"},\n   748→\t\t\t\t},\n   749→\t\t\t\tTo: \"merge\",\n   750→\t\t\t},\n   751→\t\t},\n   752→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n   753→\t}\n   754→\n   755→\terr := wf.Validate()\n   756→\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n   757→}\n   758→\n   759→func TestWorkflow_Validate_CollectBadStep(t *testing.T) {\n   760→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   761→\t\tName: \"bad-collect\",\n   762→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   763→\t\t\t\"code\": {Name: \"code\", Type: domain.StepTypeAgent, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   764→\t\t},\n   765→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   766→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   767→\t\t},\n   768→\t\tCollects: []domain.Collect{\n   769→\t\t\t{\n   770→\t\t\t\tMode:       domain.CollectAll,\n   771→\t\t\t\tConditions: []domain.WireCondition{{Step: \"nonexistent\", Result: \"success\"}},\n   772→\t\t\t\tTo:         \"code\",\n   773→\t\t\t},\n   774→\t\t},\n   775→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n   776→\t}\n   777→\n   778→\terr := wf.Validate()\n   779→\trequire.Error(t, err)\n   780→\tassert.Contains(t, err.Error(), \"nonexistent\")\n   781→}\n   782→\n   783→func TestWorkflow_Validate_CollectBadTarget(t *testing.T) {\n   784→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   785→\t\tName: \"bad-target\",\n   786→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   787→\t\t\t\"code\": {Name: \"code\", Type: domain.StepTypeAgent, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   788→\t\t},\n   789→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   790→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   791→\t\t},\n   792→\t\tCollects: []domain.Collect{\n   793→\t\t\t{\n   794→\t\t\t\tMode:       domain.CollectAll,\n   795→\t\t\t\tConditions: []domain.WireCondition{{Step: \"code\", Result: \"success\"}},\n   796→\t\t\t\tTo:         \"nonexistent\",\n   797→\t\t\t},\n   798→\t\t},\n   799→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n   800→\t}\n   801→\n   802→\terr := wf.Validate()\n   803→\trequire.Error(t, err)\n   804→\tassert.Contains(t, err.Error(), \"nonexistent\")\n   805→}\n   806→```\n   807→\n   808→**Step 2: Run to verify they fail**\n   809→\n   810→Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -run \"TestWorkflow_Validate_Collect\" -v`\n   811→Expected: `TestWorkflow_Validate_CollectValid` may pass (no validation yet = no rejection), but `CollectBadStep` and `CollectBadTarget` will fail (no error returned).\n   812→\n   813→**Step 3: Update Validate method**\n   814→\n   815→In the `Validate()` method in `workflow.go`, after the existing wired-results check, add:\n   816→\n   817→1. Count results covered by collects (so they satisfy the \"every result must be wired\" check).\n   818→2. Validate collect conditions reference real steps and declared results.\n   819→3. Validate collect targets exist.\n   820→\n   821→```go\n   822→// After building the wired map, also count results covered by collects\n   823→for _, c := range w.Collects {\n   824→\t// Validate target step exists\n   825→\tif c.To != StepDone && c.To != StepAbort {\n   826→\t\tif _, ok := w.Steps[c.To]; !ok {\n   827→\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"workflow %q: collect target step %q not found\", w.Name, c.To)\n   828→\t\t}\n   829→\t\treachable[c.To] = true\n   830→\t}\n   831→\n   832→\tfor _, cond := range c.Conditions {\n   833→\t\t// Validate condition step exists\n   834→\t\tstep, ok := w.Steps[cond.Step]\n   835→\t\tif !ok {\n   836→\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"workflow %q: collect references unknown step %q\", w.Name, cond.Step)\n   837→\t\t}\n   838→\t\t// Validate condition result is declared\n   839→\t\tfound := false\n   840→\t\tfor _, r := range step.Results {\n   841→\t\t\tif r == cond.Result {\n   842→\t\t\t\tfound = true\n   843→\t\t\t\tbreak\n   844→\t\t\t}\n   845→\t\t}\n   846→\t\tif !found {\n   847→\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"workflow %q: collect references undeclared result %q on step %q\", w.Name, cond.Result, cond.Step)\n   848→\t\t}\n   849→\t\t// Mark as wired\n   850→\t\tif wired[cond.Step] == nil {\n   851→\t\t\twired[cond.Step] = make(map[string]bool)\n   852→\t\t}\n   853→\t\twired[cond.Step][cond.Result] = true\n   854→\t}\n   855→}\n   856→```\n   857→\n   858→**Step 4: Run all domain tests**\n   859→\n   860→Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -v`\n   861→Expected: all PASS.\n   862→\n   863→**Step 5: Commit**\n   864→\n   865→```bash\n   866→git add internal/domain/workflow.go internal/domain/workflow_test.go\n   867→git commit -m \"feat(domain): validate collect conditions and targets\"\n   868→```\n   869→\n   870→---\n   871→\n   872→### Task 8: Rewrite engine as DAG walker\n   873→\n   874→**Files:**\n   875→- Modify: `internal/engine/engine.go`\n   876→- Modify: `internal/engine/engine_test.go`\n   877→\n   878→This is the largest task. The engine changes from a single-step loop to a concurrent DAG walker.\n   879→\n   880→**Step 1: Write failing tests for fanout and collect**\n   881→\n   882→Add to `engine_test.go`:\n   883→\n   884→```go\n   885→func TestEngine_Fanout(t *testing.T) {\n   886→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   887→\t\tName: \"fanout\",\n   888→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   889→\t\t\t\"code\": {Name: \"code\", Type: domain.StepTypeAgent, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   890→\t\t\t\"test\": {Name: \"test\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   891→\t\t\t\"lint\": {Name: \"lint\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   892→\t\t},\n   893→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   894→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: \"test\"},\n   895→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: \"lint\"},\n   896→\t\t\t{From: \"test\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   897→\t\t\t{From: \"lint\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   898→\t\t},\n   899→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n   900→\t}\n   901→\n   902→\texec := &fakeExecutor{results: map[string]string{\n   903→\t\t\"code\": \"success\", \"test\": \"success\", \"lint\": \"success\",\n   904→\t}}\n   905→\teng := engine.New(exec)\n   906→\n   907→\trun, err := eng.Run(context.Background(), wf)\n   908→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   909→\tassert.Equal(t, domain.RunStateSucceeded, run.State)\n   910→\tassert.Contains(t, exec.called, \"code\")\n   911→\tassert.Contains(t, exec.called, \"test\")\n   912→\tassert.Contains(t, exec.called, \"lint\")\n   913→}\n   914→\n   915→func TestEngine_CollectAll(t *testing.T) {\n   916→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   917→\t\tName: \"collect-all\",\n   918→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   919→\t\t\t\"code\":  {Name: \"code\", Type: domain.StepTypeAgent, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   920→\t\t\t\"test\":  {Name: \"test\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   921→\t\t\t\"lint\":  {Name: \"lint\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   922→\t\t\t\"merge\": {Name: \"merge\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   923→\t\t},\n   924→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   925→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: \"test\"},\n   926→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: \"lint\"},\n   927→\t\t\t{From: \"merge\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   928→\t\t},\n   929→\t\tCollects: []domain.Collect{\n   930→\t\t\t{\n   931→\t\t\t\tMode: domain.CollectAll,\n   932→\t\t\t\tConditions: []domain.WireCondition{\n   933→\t\t\t\t\t{Step: \"test\", Result: \"success\"},\n   934→\t\t\t\t\t{Step: \"lint\", Result: \"success\"},\n   935→\t\t\t\t},\n   936→\t\t\t\tTo: \"merge\",\n   937→\t\t\t},\n   938→\t\t},\n   939→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n   940→\t}\n   941→\n   942→\texec := &fakeExecutor{results: map[string]string{\n   943→\t\t\"code\": \"success\", \"test\": \"success\", \"lint\": \"success\", \"merge\": \"success\",\n   944→\t}}\n   945→\teng := engine.New(exec)\n   946→\n   947→\trun, err := eng.Run(context.Background(), wf)\n   948→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   949→\tassert.Equal(t, domain.RunStateSucceeded, run.State)\n   950→\tassert.Contains(t, exec.called, \"merge\")\n   951→}\n   952→\n   953→func TestEngine_CollectAny(t *testing.T) {\n   954→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   955→\t\tName: \"collect-any\",\n   956→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   957→\t\t\t\"fast\":  {Name: \"fast\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   958→\t\t\t\"slow\":  {Name: \"slow\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   959→\t\t\t\"next\":  {Name: \"next\", Type: domain.StepTypeScript, Results: []string{\"success\"}},\n   960→\t\t},\n   961→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   962→\t\t\t{From: \"fast\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   963→\t\t\t{From: \"slow\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   964→\t\t\t{From: \"next\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   965→\t\t},\n   966→\t\tCollects: []domain.Collect{\n   967→\t\t\t{\n   968→\t\t\t\tMode: domain.CollectAny,\n   969→\t\t\t\tConditions: []domain.WireCondition{\n   970→\t\t\t\t\t{Step: \"fast\", Result: \"success\"},\n   971→\t\t\t\t\t{Step: \"slow\", Result: \"success\"},\n   972→\t\t\t\t},\n   973→\t\t\t\tTo: \"next\",\n   974→\t\t\t},\n   975→\t\t},\n   976→\t\tEntryStep: \"fast\",\n   977→\t}\n   978→\n   979→\t// fast and slow both started somehow (need fanout to entry for this to work)\n   980→\t// For simplicity, test with sequential: fast completes, any-collect fires\n   981→\texec := &fakeExecutor{results: map[string]string{\n   982→\t\t\"fast\": \"success\", \"slow\": \"success\", \"next\": \"success\",\n   983→\t}}\n   984→\teng := engine.New(exec)\n   985→\n   986→\trun, err := eng.Run(context.Background(), wf)\n   987→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n   988→\tassert.Equal(t, domain.RunStateSucceeded, run.State)\n   989→\tassert.Contains(t, exec.called, \"next\")\n   990→}\n   991→\n   992→func TestEngine_UndeclaredResultAborts(t *testing.T) {\n   993→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   994→\t\tName: \"undeclared\",\n   995→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   996→\t\t\t\"code\": {Name: \"code\", Type: domain.StepTypeAgent, Results: []string{\"success\", \"fail\"}},\n   997→\t\t},\n   998→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   999→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n  1000→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"fail\", To: domain.StepAbort},\n  1001→\t\t},\n  1002→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n  1003→\t}\n  1004→\n  1005→\t// Return a result not in declared list\n  1006→\texec := &fakeExecutor{results: map[string]string{\"code\": \"unknown\"}}\n  1007→\teng := engine.New(exec)\n  1008→\n  1009→\trun, err := eng.Run(context.Background(), wf)\n  1010→\trequire.Error(t, err)\n  1011→\tassert.Equal(t, domain.RunStateFailed, run.State)\n  1012→\tassert.Contains(t, err.Error(), \"undeclared\")\n  1013→}\n  1014→```\n  1015→\n  1016→Note: the `fakeExecutor` needs to be made thread-safe for concurrent access. Update it:\n  1017→\n  1018→```go\n  1019→type fakeExecutor struct {\n  1020→\tmu      sync.Mutex\n  1021→\tresults map[string]string\n  1022→\tcalled  []string\n  1023→}\n  1024→\n  1025→func (f *fakeExecutor) Execute(_ context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error) {\n  1026→\tf.mu.Lock()\n  1027→\tdefer f.mu.Unlock()\n  1028→\tf.called = append(f.called, step.Name)\n  1029→\treturn f.results[step.Name], nil\n  1030→}\n  1031→```\n  1032→\n  1033→**Step 2: Run to verify they fail**\n  1034→\n  1035→Run: `go test ./internal/engine/ -run \"TestEngine_Fanout|TestEngine_Collect|TestEngine_Undeclared\" -v`\n  1036→Expected: FAIL — engine doesn't support fanout/collect.\n  1037→\n  1038→**Step 3: Rewrite engine**\n  1039→\n  1040→Replace the `Run` method in `engine.go` with the DAG walker. Key changes:\n  1041→\n  1042→1. Track `active` step count, `completed` map, and `pending` collect states.\n  1043→2. Use a results channel for step completion notifications.\n  1044→3. When a step completes: validate result is declared, look up simple wires via `NextSteps`, check collect conditions, launch new steps.\n  1045→4. Terminate when active count hits 0.\n  1046→5. Track terminal states — all `done` = succeeded, any `abort` = failed.\n  1047→\n  1048→The full implementation involves:\n  1049→- A `stepResult` struct sent on the channel: `{stepName, result, err}`.\n  1050→- A `launchStep` helper that increments active count and starts a goroutine.\n  1051→- The main loop: receive from channel, process result, launch new steps.\n  1052→- Collect state tracking: for each `Collect`, a set of satisfied condition indices.\n  1053→\n  1054→The existing `StatusHandler` interface stays the same — `OnStepStart`/`OnStepComplete` are called per step as before.\n  1055→\n  1056→**Step 4: Run all engine tests**\n  1057→\n  1058→Run: `go test ./internal/engine/ -v`\n  1059→Expected: all PASS (both old and new tests).\n  1060→\n  1061→**Step 5: Commit**\n  1062→\n  1063→```bash\n  1064→git add internal/engine/engine.go internal/engine/engine_test.go\n  1065→git commit -m \"feat(engine): rewrite as concurrent DAG walker with fanout/collect\"\n  1066→```\n  1067→\n  1068→---\n  1069→\n  1070→### Task 9: Update Run model for concurrent steps\n  1071→\n  1072→**Files:**\n  1073→- Modify: `internal/domain/run.go`\n  1074→\n  1075→**Step 1: Replace `CurrentStep` with `ActiveSteps`**\n  1076→\n  1077→Change the `Run` struct:\n  1078→\n  1079→```go\n  1080→type Run struct {\n  1081→\tID             string\n  1082→\tWorkflowName   string\n  1083→\tState          RunState\n  1084→\tActiveSteps    []string  // replaces CurrentStep\n  1085→\tStepExecutions []*StepExecution\n  1086→\tStartedAt      time.Time\n  1087→\tCompletedAt    time.Time\n  1088→}\n  1089→```\n  1090→\n  1091→Update `RecordStepStart` to append to `ActiveSteps` instead of overwriting `CurrentStep`. Update `RecordStepComplete` to remove from `ActiveSteps`.\n  1092→\n  1093→**Step 2: Verify it compiles and tests pass**\n  1094→\n  1095→Run: `go test ./... 2>&1 | tail -20`\n  1096→\n  1097→Fix any compilation errors from callers that reference `CurrentStep` (likely the engine and runner). Update them to use `ActiveSteps`.\n  1098→\n  1099→**Step 3: Commit**\n  1100→\n  1101→```bash\n  1102→git add internal/domain/run.go\n  1103→git commit -m \"feat(domain): replace CurrentStep with ActiveSteps for concurrency\"\n  1104→```\n  1105→\n  1106→---\n  1107→\n  1108→### Task 10: Update runner and status reporting\n  1109→\n  1110→**Files:**\n  1111→- Modify: `internal/agent/runner.go`\n  1112→\n  1113→**Step 1: Verify runner compiles with new engine API**\n  1114→\n  1115→The runner creates the engine and calls `eng.Run()`. The engine's API (`Run(ctx, wf)`) hasn't changed — the concurrency is internal. The `stepExecutor` and `statusReporter` interfaces are unchanged.\n  1116→\n  1117→Run: `go build ./internal/agent/...`\n  1118→Expected: success. If `CurrentStep` was referenced, update to `ActiveSteps`.\n  1119→\n  1120→**Step 2: Run full test suite**\n  1121→\n  1122→Run: `go test ./... -v 2>&1 | tail -40`\n  1123→Expected: all PASS.\n  1124→\n  1125→**Step 3: Commit if any changes were needed**\n  1126→\n  1127→```bash\n  1128→git add internal/agent/runner.go\n  1129→git commit -m \"fix(runner): adapt to concurrent engine and ActiveSteps\"\n  1130→```\n  1131→\n  1132→---\n  1133→\n  1134→### Task 11: Update example workflows\n  1135→\n  1136→**Files:**\n  1137→- Modify: `examples/ruby-calculator/develop.cloche`\n  1138→- Modify: `examples/hello-world/build.cloche` (if it uses `pass`)\n  1139→- Modify: `examples/hello-world/flaky.cloche` (if it uses `pass`)\n  1140→\n  1141→**Step 1: Update ruby-calculator**\n  1142→\n  1143→Change `results = [pass, fail]` to `results = [success, fail]` in `test` and `lint` steps. Update wiring from `test:pass` → `test:success` and `lint:pass` → `lint:success`. Change `fix` step results from `[fixed, give-up]` to `[success, fail, give-up]` (or keep custom names — the prompt adapter will emit markers). Actually, keep `[fixed, give-up]` since those are custom edges that require markers.\n  1144→\n  1145→Wait — the fix step currently returns `\"fixed\"` via `resultOrDefault` (exit 0, first result). With the new protocol, exit 0 = `\"success\"`, which isn't declared. The fix step needs updating. Options:\n  1146→- Change results to `[success, fail, give-up]` and wiring to `fix:success -> test`.\n  1147→- Or have the prompt inject result instructions so the LLM emits `CLOCHE_RESULT:fixed`.\n  1148→\n  1149→The cleaner approach: rename to `[success, fail, give-up]` since `\"fixed\"` was just a synonym for success. Update wiring accordingly.\n  1150→\n  1151→```\n  1152→step fix {\n  1153→    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n  1154→    max_attempts = \"2\"\n  1155→    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  1156→}\n  1157→\n  1158→fix:success -> test\n  1159→fix:fail -> abort\n  1160→fix:give-up -> abort\n  1161→```\n  1162→\n  1163→Similarly, `implement` step: change from `[success, fail]` — these already match convention.\n  1164→\n  1165→**Step 2: Update hello-world workflows if needed**\n  1166→\n  1167→Check `build.cloche` and `flaky.cloche` for `pass` results and update.\n  1168→\n  1169→**Step 3: Run the DSL parser on updated files to verify**\n  1170→\n  1171→Run: `go run ./cmd/cloche-agent/ --help` (or a quick parse test).\n  1172→\n  1173→**Step 4: Commit**\n  1174→\n  1175→```bash\n  1176→git add examples/\n  1177→git commit -m \"fix(examples): rename pass->success, update fix step results\"\n  1178→```\n  1179→\n  1180→---\n  1181→\n  1182→### Task 12: Full integration test pass\n  1183→\n  1184→**Files:**\n  1185→- All test files\n  1186→\n  1187→**Step 1: Run complete test suite**\n  1188→\n  1189→Run: `go test ./... -v -count=1`\n  1190→Expected: all PASS.\n  1191→\n  1192→**Step 2: Run linter if available**\n  1193→\n  1194→Run: `go vet ./...`\n  1195→Expected: no issues.\n  1196→\n  1197→**Step 3: Commit any final fixes**\n  1198→\n  1199→---\n  1200→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUnpJzSHuhmadkgcFGRrK6","session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"abc759ee-3c62-4ea7-82b8-d307faea5d4b"}
