{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EyeYXVbbGbcbgsBLKNkZHZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# `cloche init` Implementation Plan\n     2→\n     3→> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n     4→\n     5→**Goal:** Add a `cloche init` command that scaffolds a Cloche project (workflow, Dockerfile, prompt templates) in the current directory.\n     6→\n     7→**Architecture:** New `init` case in the CLI's main switch, dispatching to `cmdInit()` in a new `cmd/cloche/init.go` file. Templates are string constants with `fmt.Sprintf` substitution. No daemon connection needed.\n     8→\n     9→**Tech Stack:** Go, `os` for file I/O, `fmt.Sprintf` for templating.\n    10→\n    11→---\n    12→\n    13→### Task 1: Create `cmd/cloche/init.go` with templates and `cmdInit()`\n    14→\n    15→**Files:**\n    16→- Create: `cmd/cloche/init.go`\n    17→\n    18→**Step 1: Write `cmd/cloche/init.go`**\n    19→\n    20→```go\n    21→package main\n    22→\n    23→import (\n    24→\t\"fmt\"\n    25→\t\"os\"\n    26→\t\"path/filepath\"\n    27→\t\"strings\"\n    28→)\n    29→\n    30→var workflowTemplate = `workflow \"%s\" {\n    31→  step implement {\n    32→    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    33→    results = [success, fail]\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  step test {\n    37→    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    38→    results = [success, fail]\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  step fix {\n    42→    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    43→    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    44→    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  implement:success -> test\n    48→  implement:fail -> abort\n    49→  test:success -> done\n    50→  test:fail -> fix\n    51→  fix:success -> test\n    52→  fix:fail -> abort\n    53→  fix:give-up -> abort\n    54→}\n    55→`\n    56→\n    57→var dockerfileTemplate = `FROM golang:1.25 AS cloche-builder\n    58→WORKDIR /src\n    59→COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n    60→RUN go mod download\n    61→COPY . .\n    62→RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o /cloche-agent ./cmd/cloche-agent\n    63→\n    64→FROM %s\n    65→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y git nodejs npm && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    66→RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n    67→COPY --from=cloche-builder /cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/cloche-agent\n    68→RUN useradd -m -s /bin/bash agent\n    69→WORKDIR /workspace\n    70→RUN chown agent:agent /workspace\n    71→USER agent\n    72→`\n    73→\n    74→var implementPrompt = `Implement the following change in this project.\n    75→\n    76→## User Request\n    77→(Contents of .cloche/prompt.txt will be injected here by the adapter)\n    78→\n    79→## Guidelines\n    80→- Follow existing project conventions if files already exist\n    81→- Write tests for new functionality\n    82→- Run tests locally before declaring success\n    83→`\n    84→\n    85→var fixPrompt = `Fix the code based on the validation failures below.\n    86→Only modify files that need fixing. Do not rewrite the entire project.\n    87→\n    88→## Validation Output\n    89→(Contents of .cloche/output/*.log will be injected here by the adapter)\n    90→`\n    91→\n    92→func cmdInit(args []string) {\n    93→\tworkflow := \"develop\"\n    94→\timage := \"ubuntu:24.04\"\n    95→\n    96→\tfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n    97→\t\tswitch args[i] {\n    98→\t\tcase \"--workflow\":\n    99→\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   100→\t\t\t\ti++\n   101→\t\t\t\tworkflow = args[i]\n   102→\t\t\t}\n   103→\t\tcase \"--image\":\n   104→\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   105→\t\t\t\ti++\n   106→\t\t\t\timage = args[i]\n   107→\t\t\t}\n   108→\t\t}\n   109→\t}\n   110→\n   111→\tworkflowFile := workflow + \".cloche\"\n   112→\n   113→\t// Refuse to overwrite existing workflow\n   114→\tif _, err := os.Stat(workflowFile); err == nil {\n   115→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %s already exists\\n\", workflowFile)\n   116→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   117→\t}\n   118→\n   119→\t// Create prompts directory\n   120→\tif err := os.MkdirAll(\"prompts\", 0755); err != nil {\n   121→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error creating prompts/: %v\\n\", err)\n   122→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   123→\t}\n   124→\n   125→\t// Write all files\n   126→\tfiles := map[string]string{\n   127→\t\tworkflowFile:            fmt.Sprintf(workflowTemplate, workflow),\n   128→\t\t\"Dockerfile\":            fmt.Sprintf(dockerfileTemplate, image),\n   129→\t\t\"prompts/implement.md\":  implementPrompt,\n   130→\t\t\"prompts/fix.md\":        fixPrompt,\n   131→\t}\n   132→\n   133→\tfor path, content := range files {\n   134→\t\tif _, err := os.Stat(path); err == nil {\n   135→\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  skip %s (already exists)\\n\", path)\n   136→\t\t\tcontinue\n   137→\t\t}\n   138→\t\tif err := os.WriteFile(path, []byte(content), 0644); err != nil {\n   139→\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error writing %s: %v\\n\", path, err)\n   140→\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   141→\t\t}\n   142→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  create %s\\n\", path)\n   143→\t}\n   144→\n   145→\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n   146→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"\\nInitialized Cloche project in %s\\n\", filepath.Base(cwd))\n   147→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"\\nNext steps:\\n\")\n   148→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  1. Edit %s — change the test command for your project\\n\", workflowFile)\n   149→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  2. Edit Dockerfile — add your project's dependencies\\n\")\n   150→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  3. docker build -t cloche-agent .\\n\")\n   151→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  4. cloche run --workflow %s --prompt \\\"...\\\"\\n\", workflow)\n   152→}\n   153→```\n   154→\n   155→Note: The `files` map iteration order is non-deterministic, but that's fine —\n   156→the output order of \"create\" messages doesn't matter.\n   157→\n   158→**Step 2: Verify it compiles**\n   159→\n   160→Run: `go build ./cmd/cloche/`\n   161→Expected: Compile error — `cmdInit` not wired into `main.go` yet. That's fine,\n   162→confirms the file parses.\n   163→\n   164→Actually this will compile since `cmdInit` is defined but not yet called.\n   165→Expected: Success, no errors.\n   166→\n   167→**Step 3: Commit**\n   168→\n   169→```\n   170→git add cmd/cloche/init.go\n   171→git commit -m \"feat(cli): add init command templates\"\n   172→```\n   173→\n   174→---\n   175→\n   176→### Task 2: Wire `init` into `cmd/cloche/main.go`\n   177→\n   178→**Files:**\n   179→- Modify: `cmd/cloche/main.go`\n   180→\n   181→**Step 1: Add `init` case to the switch and usage text**\n   182→\n   183→In `main()`, add the `init` case **before** the gRPC connection setup (since\n   184→init doesn't need a daemon). Restructure so that `init` is handled early:\n   185→\n   186→```go\n   187→func main() {\n   188→\tif len(os.Args) < 2 {\n   189→\t\tusage()\n   190→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   191→\t}\n   192→\n   193→\t// Commands that don't need a daemon connection\n   194→\tswitch os.Args[1] {\n   195→\tcase \"init\":\n   196→\t\tcmdInit(os.Args[2:])\n   197→\t\treturn\n   198→\t}\n   199→\n   200→\t// Commands that need a daemon connection\n   201→\taddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_ADDR\")\n   202→\t// ... rest unchanged\n   203→```\n   204→\n   205→Update `usage()` to include `init`:\n   206→\n   207→```go\n   208→func usage() {\n   209→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, `usage: cloche <command> [args]\n   210→\n   211→Commands:\n   212→  init [--workflow <name>] [--image <base>]  Initialize a Cloche project\n   213→  run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"]      Launch a workflow run\n   214→  status <run-id>                             Check run status\n   215→  list                                        List all runs\n   216→  stop <run-id>                               Stop a running workflow\n   217→`)\n   218→}\n   219→```\n   220→\n   221→**Step 2: Verify it compiles**\n   222→\n   223→Run: `go build ./cmd/cloche/`\n   224→Expected: Success\n   225→\n   226→**Step 3: Commit**\n   227→\n   228→```\n   229→git add cmd/cloche/main.go\n   230→git commit -m \"feat(cli): wire init subcommand into CLI dispatch\"\n   231→```\n   232→\n   233→---\n   234→\n   235→### Task 3: Write tests for `cmdInit`\n   236→\n   237→**Files:**\n   238→- Create: `cmd/cloche/init_test.go`\n   239→\n   240→**Step 1: Write tests**\n   241→\n   242→```go\n   243→package main\n   244→\n   245→import (\n   246→\t\"os\"\n   247→\t\"path/filepath\"\n   248→\t\"testing\"\n   249→)\n   250→\n   251→func TestCmdInit_DefaultFlags(t *testing.T) {\n   252→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n   253→\torigDir, _ := os.Getwd()\n   254→\tos.Chdir(dir)\n   255→\tdefer os.Chdir(origDir)\n   256→\n   257→\tcmdInit([]string{})\n   258→\n   259→\t// Verify all files created\n   260→\tfor _, path := range []string{\n   261→\t\t\"develop.cloche\",\n   262→\t\t\"Dockerfile\",\n   263→\t\t\"prompts/implement.md\",\n   264→\t\t\"prompts/fix.md\",\n   265→\t} {\n   266→\t\tif _, err := os.Stat(path); os.IsNotExist(err) {\n   267→\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected %s to exist\", path)\n   268→\t\t}\n   269→\t}\n   270→\n   271→\t// Verify workflow name is embedded\n   272→\tdata, _ := os.ReadFile(\"develop.cloche\")\n   273→\tif got := string(data); !contains(got, `workflow \"develop\"`) {\n   274→\t\tt.Errorf(\"workflow file missing workflow name, got:\\n%s\", got)\n   275→\t}\n   276→}\n   277→\n   278→func TestCmdInit_CustomFlags(t *testing.T) {\n   279→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n   280→\torigDir, _ := os.Getwd()\n   281→\tos.Chdir(dir)\n   282→\tdefer os.Chdir(origDir)\n   283→\n   284→\tcmdInit([]string{\"--workflow\", \"build\", \"--image\", \"python:3.12\"})\n   285→\n   286→\t// Custom workflow file\n   287→\tif _, err := os.Stat(\"build.cloche\"); os.IsNotExist(err) {\n   288→\t\tt.Error(\"expected build.cloche to exist\")\n   289→\t}\n   290→\tif _, err := os.Stat(\"develop.cloche\"); err == nil {\n   291→\t\tt.Error(\"develop.cloche should not exist with --workflow build\")\n   292→\t}\n   293→\n   294→\t// Custom image in Dockerfile\n   295→\tdata, _ := os.ReadFile(\"Dockerfile\")\n   296→\tif !contains(string(data), \"FROM python:3.12\") {\n   297→\t\tt.Error(\"Dockerfile should contain custom base image\")\n   298→\t}\n   299→}\n   300→\n   301→func TestCmdInit_SkipsExistingFiles(t *testing.T) {\n   302→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n   303→\torigDir, _ := os.Getwd()\n   304→\tos.Chdir(dir)\n   305→\tdefer os.Chdir(origDir)\n   306→\n   307→\t// Pre-create Dockerfile with custom content\n   308→\tos.WriteFile(\"Dockerfile\", []byte(\"custom\"), 0644)\n   309→\n   310→\tcmdInit([]string{})\n   311→\n   312→\t// Dockerfile should NOT be overwritten\n   313→\tdata, _ := os.ReadFile(\"Dockerfile\")\n   314→\tif string(data) != \"custom\" {\n   315→\t\tt.Error(\"existing Dockerfile was overwritten\")\n   316→\t}\n   317→\n   318→\t// Other files should still be created\n   319→\tif _, err := os.Stat(\"develop.cloche\"); os.IsNotExist(err) {\n   320→\t\tt.Error(\"develop.cloche should still be created\")\n   321→\t}\n   322→}\n   323→\n   324→func TestCmdInit_RefusesExistingWorkflow(t *testing.T) {\n   325→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n   326→\torigDir, _ := os.Getwd()\n   327→\tos.Chdir(dir)\n   328→\tdefer os.Chdir(origDir)\n   329→\n   330→\t// Pre-create the workflow file\n   331→\tos.WriteFile(\"develop.cloche\", []byte(\"existing\"), 0644)\n   332→\n   333→\t// cmdInit calls os.Exit(1) when workflow exists.\n   334→\t// We can't easily test os.Exit, so just verify the file check logic.\n   335→\tif _, err := os.Stat(\"develop.cloche\"); os.IsNotExist(err) {\n   336→\t\tt.Error(\"precondition failed: workflow file should exist\")\n   337→\t}\n   338→}\n   339→\n   340→func contains(s, substr string) bool {\n   341→\treturn filepath.Base(s) != \"\" && // unused, just to avoid import error\n   342→\t\tlen(s) >= len(substr) &&\n   343→\t\tstringContains(s, substr)\n   344→}\n   345→\n   346→func stringContains(s, sub string) bool {\n   347→\tfor i := 0; i <= len(s)-len(sub); i++ {\n   348→\t\tif s[i:i+len(sub)] == sub {\n   349→\t\t\treturn true\n   350→\t\t}\n   351→\t}\n   352→\treturn false\n   353→}\n   354→```\n   355→\n   356→Note: `TestCmdInit_RefusesExistingWorkflow` can't easily test `os.Exit(1)`.\n   357→It just verifies the precondition. The real guard is tested manually.\n   358→\n   359→**Step 2: Run tests**\n   360→\n   361→Run: `go test ./cmd/cloche/ -v -run TestCmdInit`\n   362→Expected: All PASS\n   363→\n   364→**Step 3: Commit**\n   365→\n   366→```\n   367→git add cmd/cloche/init_test.go\n   368→git commit -m \"test(cli): add tests for cloche init\"\n   369→```\n   370→\n   371→---\n   372→\n   373→### Task 4: Manual verification\n   374→\n   375→**Step 1: Build the binary**\n   376→\n   377→Run: `go install ./cmd/cloche`\n   378→\n   379→**Step 2: Test in a temp directory**\n   380→\n   381→```\n   382→mkdir /tmp/test-init && cd /tmp/test-init\n   383→cloche init\n   384→```\n   385→\n   386→Expected output:\n   387→```\n   388→  create develop.cloche\n   389→  create Dockerfile\n   390→  create prompts/implement.md\n   391→  create prompts/fix.md\n   392→\n   393→Initialized Cloche project in test-init\n   394→\n   395→Next steps:\n   396→  1. Edit develop.cloche — change the test command for your project\n   397→  2. Edit Dockerfile — add your project's dependencies\n   398→  3. docker build -t cloche-agent .\n   399→  4. cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"...\"\n   400→```\n   401→\n   402→**Step 3: Test with flags**\n   403→\n   404→```\n   405→rm -rf /tmp/test-init && mkdir /tmp/test-init && cd /tmp/test-init\n   406→cloche init --workflow build --image python:3.12\n   407→```\n   408→\n   409→Verify `build.cloche` exists with `workflow \"build\"`, Dockerfile has `FROM python:3.12`.\n   410→\n   411→**Step 4: Test refusal**\n   412→\n   413→```\n   414→cloche init\n   415→```\n   416→\n   417→Expected: `error: build.cloche already exists` (exit 1) — wait, the workflow\n   418→is `develop` by default but we created `build.cloche`. So this should create\n   419→`develop.cloche` fine. Test with:\n   420→\n   421→```\n   422→cloche init --workflow build\n   423→```\n   424→\n   425→Expected: `error: build.cloche already exists`\n   426→\n   427→**Step 5: Cleanup**\n   428→\n   429→```\n   430→rm -rf /tmp/test-init\n   431→```\n   432→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUnpJzSHuhmadkgcFGRrK6","session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"3dadc53f-96d0-4825-bf95-753983e61498"}
