{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01QLiLXeChRYqYxYkiCjr52Q","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Mwmj6bFXX3jC6suvZAkpkq","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-design.md","limit":100},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25112,"cache_read_input_tokens":39261,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":25112,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUnpJzSHuhmadkgcFGRrK6","session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"d70197fb-7228-4b70-93f1-a429d6791546"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Mwmj6bFXX3jC6suvZAkpkq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Subdirectory Layout, Daemon-Side Extraction, and Poll Command\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-01\n     4→\n     5→## Overview\n     6→\n     7→Three related changes to Cloche:\n     8→\n     9→1. Move cloche project files into a `./cloche/` subdirectory of the host project, separating host-level files (CLAUDE.md, .git, build config) from agent-level files.\n    10→2. Replace the in-container git push mechanism with daemon-side result extraction using `docker cp` and host-side git operations (with worktrees for concurrency).\n    11→3. Add a `poll` command that blocks until a run reaches a terminal state or its container has been dead for >1 minute.\n    12→\n    13→## 1. Directory Layout\n    14→\n    15→### Host project (user's repo root)\n    16→\n    17→```\n    18→my-project/\n    19→├── .git/\n    20→├── .gitignore\n    21→├── .gitworktrees/         # Daemon-managed git worktrees (gitignored)\n    22→├── CLAUDE.md              # Host-level agent instructions\n    23→├── README.md\n    24→├── cloche/                # Everything cloche manages\n    25→│   ├── develop.cloche     # Workflow DSL file(s)\n    26→│   ├── Dockerfile\n    27→│   ├── CLAUDE.md          # Inner agent instructions\n    28→│   ├── .cloche/\n    29→│   │   ├── config\n    30→│   │   ├── prompts/\n    31→│   │   │   ├── implement.md\n    32→│   │   │   └── fix.md\n    33→│   │   ├── <run-id>/      # Per-run output (gitignored)\n    34→│   │   │   ├── prompt.txt\n    35→│   │   │   └── output/\n    36→│   │   └── ...\n    37→│   └── <source files>     # Project code the agent works on\n    38→└── <host-level files>\n    39→```\n    40→\n    41→### Inside the container\n    42→\n    43→```\n    44→/workspace/                # = contents of host's ./cloche/\n    45→├── develop.cloche\n    46→├── Dockerfile\n    47→├── CLAUDE.md\n    48→├── .cloche/\n    49→│   ├── config\n    50→│   ├── prompts/\n    51→│   └── ...\n    52→└── <source files>\n    53→```\n    54→\n    55→The container sees a flat `/workspace/` — the contents of `./cloche/` are copied directly, not nested.\n    56→\n    57→### Gitignore additions\n    58→\n    59→`cloche init` adds to the host `.gitignore`:\n    60→\n    61→```\n    62→cloche/.cloche/*/\n    63→.gitworktrees/\n    64→```\n    65→\n    66→This ignores per-run output directories and worktrees, but keeps `cloche/.cloche/config` and `cloche/.cloche/prompts/` tracked.\n    67→\n    68→## 2. Container Lifecycle and Result Extraction\n    69→\n    70→### Run start\n    71→\n    72→1. The daemon records `base_sha` = current HEAD of the host repo.\n    73→2. `base_sha` is stored in the run record (new column in SQLite `runs` table).\n    74→3. `docker cp <host>/cloche/. <container>:/workspace/`\n    75→4. Container starts; agent runs the workflow autonomously.\n    76→\n    77→### Run completion\n    78→\n    79→When the container exits (success or failure):\n    80→\n    81→1. **Copy out:** `docker cp <container>:/workspace/. <tempdir>/`\n    82→2. **Create worktree:** `git worktree add --detach <project>/.gitworktrees/cloche/<run-id> <base_sha>`\n    83→3. **Populate:** Copy `<tempdir>` contents into `<worktree>/cloche/`\n    84→4. **Commit:**\n    85→   - `git checkout -b cloche/<run-id>` (in the worktree)\n    86→   - `git add cloche/`\n    87→   - `git commit -m \"cloche run <run-id>: <workflow-name> (<result>)\"`\n    88→5. **Cleanup:**\n    89→   - `git worktree remove <worktree-dir>`\n    90→   - Remove temp dir\n    91→   - Remove container (unless `--keep-container`)\n    92→\n    93→### Concurrency\n    94→\n    95→Each extraction uses its own git worktree at `<project>/.gitworktrees/cloche/<run-id>/`. Multiple extractions can run concurrently with no locking.\n    96→\n    97→### Error handling\n    98→\n    99→- If the container crashes, still attempt `docker cp` (the container filesystem persists until `docker rm`).\n   100→- If git operations fail, log the error, keep the container for debugging, and don't delete the temp dir."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUnpJzSHuhmadkgcFGRrK6","session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"e0da3def-fb24-42c4-9a73-f6d87a98283b"}
