{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018kYnfkv6MkMDXKsh6fDGAa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Step Timeout Design\n     2→\n     3→## Problem\n     4→\n     5→Agent steps can hang indefinitely (e.g. Claude Code waiting on a plugin server\n     6→that doesn't exist in the container). The engine has no timeout mechanism, so\n     7→the run stays in \"running\" state forever.\n     8→\n     9→## Design\n    10→\n    11→### DSL Syntax\n    12→\n    13→Per-step `timeout` key, parsed like any other config value:\n    14→\n    15→```hcl\n    16→step implement {\n    17→    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    18→    timeout = \"45m\"\n    19→    results = [success, fail]\n    20→}\n    21→```\n    22→\n    23→Accepts any `time.ParseDuration` value (e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"1h\"`, `\"90s\"`).\n    24→\n    25→### Engine Changes\n    26→\n    27→Add a `defaultTimeout` field to `Engine` (default 30m), settable via\n    28→`SetDefaultTimeout(d time.Duration)`.\n    29→\n    30→In `launchStep`, wrap `executor.Execute` with a per-step context:\n    31→\n    32→```go\n    33→go func(s *domain.Step) {\n    34→    stepCtx := ctx\n    35→    if d, ok := stepTimeout(s, e.defaultTimeout); ok {\n    36→        var cancel context.CancelFunc\n    37→        stepCtx, cancel = context.WithTimeout(ctx, d)\n    38→        defer cancel()\n    39→    }\n    40→    result, err := e.executor.Execute(stepCtx, s)\n    41→    results <- stepResult{stepName: s.Name, result: result, err: err}\n    42→}(step)\n    43→```\n    44→\n    45→`stepTimeout(step, default)` returns the step's configured timeout or the\n    46→default. It parses `step.Config[\"timeout\"]` via `time.ParseDuration`.\n    47→\n    48→### Timeout Behavior\n    49→\n    50→When the deadline fires:\n    51→1. `exec.CommandContext` kills the subprocess\n    52→2. `cmd.Run()` returns an error\n    53→3. The adapter returns `(\"fail\", err)`\n    54→4. The engine routes via existing `fail` wiring\n    55→\n    56→No new result type needed.\n    57→\n    58→### Config Key Validation\n    59→\n    60→Add a known-key registry to `Workflow.Validate()`. Each step's `Config` keys\n    61→are checked against a set of recognized keys:\n    62→\n    63→```\n    64→prompt, run, max_attempts, timeout, agent_command, agent_args,\n    65→container.* (image, network_allow, memory, agent_command, agent_args)\n    66→```\n    67→\n    68→Unrecognized keys produce a validation warning (logged to stderr), not a hard\n    69→error, to stay forward-compatible with future keys.\n    70→\n    71→### Files Changed\n    72→\n    73→| File | Change |\n    74→|------|--------|\n    75→| `internal/engine/engine.go` | `defaultTimeout` field, `SetDefaultTimeout`, `stepTimeout` helper, wrap Execute |\n    76→| `internal/engine/engine_test.go` | Test: step timeout produces \"fail\"; test: step config timeout overrides default |\n    77→| `internal/domain/workflow.go` | `ValidateConfig` method with known-key check, called from `Validate()` |\n    78→| `internal/domain/workflow_test.go` | Test: unknown config key produces warning |\n    79→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUnpJzSHuhmadkgcFGRrK6","session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"b5c026bc-efb9-4f82-9cb2-c94fc4a50509"}
