{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PMzXEFt6XKjsQHNS83B3Mt","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the four test files you requested:\n\n## `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/resume_test.go`\n\nThis test file contains two tests for the prompt adapter's resume conversation feature:\n\n- **`TestAdapter_ResumeConversation_ArgsContainDashC`**: Verifies that when `ResumeConversation` is true, the adapter returns the default args for \"claude\". It documents that the `-c` flag is prepended in `tryCommand`, not in `argsFor`, and verifies the flag ordering would include `-c` followed by `-p`.\n\n- **`TestAdapter_ResumeConversation_PromptIsRetry`**: Confirms that when `ResumeConversation` is true, the adapter's flag is set correctly (asserting the flag is true).\n\n## `/workspace/internal/engine/resume_test.go`\n\nThis test file contains five comprehensive tests for the engine's resume functionality:\n\n- **`TestEngine_ResumeFromStep`**: Tests a linear workflow (build → test → deploy) where build is preloaded; verifies that only test and deploy execute while build is skipped.\n\n- **`TestEngine_ResumeSkipsMultipleSteps`**: Tests resuming from step \"c\" in a linear workflow (a → b → c → d) with a and b preloaded; confirms only c and d execute.\n\n- **`TestEngine_ResumeWithFanout`**: Tests a fanout workflow where code has two dependents (test and lint); with code preloaded, both test and lint should execute.\n\n- **`TestEngine_ResumePreloadedStepsRecordedInRun`**: Verifies that preloaded steps still appear in the run's `StepExecutions` with their correct results.\n\n- **`TestEngine_ResumeEmptyPreloadedRunsNormally`**: Confirms that setting empty preloaded results doesn't change behavior—all steps execute normally.\n\n## `/workspace/internal/host/resume_test.go`\n\nThis test file has tests for the host runner's resume logic:\n\n- **`TestBuildPreloadedResults_LinearWorkflow`**: Tests that when resuming from \"test\" in a build → test → deploy workflow, only \"build\" is preloaded.\n\n- **`TestBuildPreloadedResults_ResumeFromFirst`**: Confirms that resuming from the entry step (\"build\") preloads nothing.\n\n- **`TestBuildPreloadedResults_MultipleCompleted`**: Tests that resuming from \"c\" in workflow a → b → c → d preloads both \"a\" and \"b\".\n\n- **`TestBuildPreloadedResults_SkipsErrorResults`**: Verifies that steps with \"error\" results are excluded from preloading, even if they appear before the resume point.\n\n- **`TestFindFirstFailedStep`**: Tests the `Run.FindFirstFailedStep()` method, verifying it finds steps with \"fail\" or \"error\" results, returns empty string for no failures.\n\n## `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help_test.go`\n\nThis test file validates the help system:\n\n- **`TestHasHelpFlag`**: Tests the `hasHelpFlag` function to detect `--help` or `-h` in arguments.\n\n- **`TestSubcommandHelpExists`**: Verifies that all expected subcommands (init, health, run, resume, status, logs, etc.) have help text defined.\n\n- **`TestSubcommandHelpContainsUsage`**: Ensures every subcommand's help text contains both \"Usage:\" and \"Examples:\" sections and includes the command name.\n\n- **`TestPrintHelp_UnknownCommand`**: Confirms `printHelp` returns true even with an unknown command.\n\n- **`TestPrintHelp_NoArgs`** and **`TestPrintHelp_ValidCommand`**: Test `printHelp` behavior.\n\n- **`TestRunHelpIncludesIssueFlag`**: Verifies the run command help documents `--issue` and `-i` flags.\n\n- **`TestListHelpIncludesTaskIdColumn`**: Checks that list command help mentions \"task ID\" column."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0a67a3f466879ca9 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 22752\ntool_uses: 4\nduration_ms: 11573</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"ff13d69a-b549-481e-b9ca-e12e2774cd6b","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read these new test files completely:\n- internal/adapters/agents/prompt/resume_test.go\n- internal/engine/resume_test.go\n- internal/host/resume_test.go\n\nAlso read the existing help_test.go: cmd/cloche/help_test.go","agentId":"a0a67a3f466879ca9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the four test files you requested:\n\n## `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/resume_test.go`\n\nThis test file contains two tests for the prompt adapter's resume conversation feature:\n\n- **`TestAdapter_ResumeConversation_ArgsContainDashC`**: Verifies that when `ResumeConversation` is true, the adapter returns the default args for \"claude\". It documents that the `-c` flag is prepended in `tryCommand`, not in `argsFor`, and verifies the flag ordering would include `-c` followed by `-p`.\n\n- **`TestAdapter_ResumeConversation_PromptIsRetry`**: Confirms that when `ResumeConversation` is true, the adapter's flag is set correctly (asserting the flag is true).\n\n## `/workspace/internal/engine/resume_test.go`\n\nThis test file contains five comprehensive tests for the engine's resume functionality:\n\n- **`TestEngine_ResumeFromStep`**: Tests a linear workflow (build → test → deploy) where build is preloaded; verifies that only test and deploy execute while build is skipped.\n\n- **`TestEngine_ResumeSkipsMultipleSteps`**: Tests resuming from step \"c\" in a linear workflow (a → b → c → d) with a and b preloaded; confirms only c and d execute.\n\n- **`TestEngine_ResumeWithFanout`**: Tests a fanout workflow where code has two dependents (test and lint); with code preloaded, both test and lint should execute.\n\n- **`TestEngine_ResumePreloadedStepsRecordedInRun`**: Verifies that preloaded steps still appear in the run's `StepExecutions` with their correct results.\n\n- **`TestEngine_ResumeEmptyPreloadedRunsNormally`**: Confirms that setting empty preloaded results doesn't change behavior—all steps execute normally.\n\n## `/workspace/internal/host/resume_test.go`\n\nThis test file has tests for the host runner's resume logic:\n\n- **`TestBuildPreloadedResults_LinearWorkflow`**: Tests that when resuming from \"test\" in a build → test → deploy workflow, only \"build\" is preloaded.\n\n- **`TestBuildPreloadedResults_ResumeFromFirst`**: Confirms that resuming from the entry step (\"build\") preloads nothing.\n\n- **`TestBuildPreloadedResults_MultipleCompleted`**: Tests that resuming from \"c\" in workflow a → b → c → d preloads both \"a\" and \"b\".\n\n- **`TestBuildPreloadedResults_SkipsErrorResults`**: Verifies that steps with \"error\" results are excluded from preloading, even if they appear before the resume point.\n\n- **`TestFindFirstFailedStep`**: Tests the `Run.FindFirstFailedStep()` method, verifying it finds steps with \"fail\" or \"error\" results, returns empty string for no failures.\n\n## `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help_test.go`\n\nThis test file validates the help system:\n\n- **`TestHasHelpFlag`**: Tests the `hasHelpFlag` function to detect `--help` or `-h` in arguments.\n\n- **`TestSubcommandHelpExists`**: Verifies that all expected subcommands (init, health, run, resume, status, logs, etc.) have help text defined.\n\n- **`TestSubcommandHelpContainsUsage`**: Ensures every subcommand's help text contains both \"Usage:\" and \"Examples:\" sections and includes the command name.\n\n- **`TestPrintHelp_UnknownCommand`**: Confirms `printHelp` returns true even with an unknown command.\n\n- **`TestPrintHelp_NoArgs`** and **`TestPrintHelp_ValidCommand`**: Test `printHelp` behavior.\n\n- **`TestRunHelpIncludesIssueFlag`**: Verifies the run command help documents `--issue` and `-i` flags.\n\n- **`TestListHelpIncludesTaskIdColumn`**: Checks that list command help mentions \"task ID\" column."}],"totalDurationMs":11573,"totalTokens":22752,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7434,"cache_read_input_tokens":14336,"output_tokens":975,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","ca