{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JBcSznxqHEKxbG5yXzGdkP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the resume command implementation. Let me compile my findings into a comprehensive report.\n\n## Resume Command Implementation Analysis\n\nI have thoroughly explored the codebase and understand the complete resume command implementation. Here's a detailed breakdown:\n\n### 1. **CLI Command Structure** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`)\n\n**Resume Command Entry Point (lines 233-258):**\n- `cmdResume()` function parses arguments: `cloche resume <run-id> [step-name]`\n- Uses gRPC metadata headers to communicate resume intent:\n  - `x-cloche-resume-run-id`: the run ID to resume\n  - `x-cloche-resume-step`: optional step name to resume from\n- Calls `client.RunWorkflow()` with an empty `RunWorkflowRequest` (resume happens via metadata, not request fields)\n\n**Help Text** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go`, lines 87-115):\n- Detailed help describing resume behavior for different step types (script, prompt, workflow)\n- Prerequisites: workflow must be in failed state, container must exist for container workflows\n- Examples provided\n\n### 2. **gRPC Proto Definition** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`)\n\n**Key Details (lines 24-28):**\n- Resume mode is handled via gRPC metadata on the `RunWorkflow` RPC (not a separate RPC)\n- No dedicated `ResumeRun` RPC; uses metadata headers instead\n- Server extracts metadata and decides whether to resume or create new run\n\n### 3. **Domain Types** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`)\n\n**Run State Management:**\n- Run states: `pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n- `StepExecution` struct tracks: step name, result, startedAt, completedAt, logs, gitRef\n- `FindFirstFailedStep()` method (lines 127-134) finds the first failed step for auto-resume\n\n**Run Fields Relevant to Resume:**\n- `State`: must be `RunStateFailed` to resume\n- `StepExecutions`: contains history of all step executions with results\n- `ContainerID`: needed for container workflow resume (must still exist)\n- `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`: needed to find workflow definition\n\n### 4. **Engine** (`/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`)\n\n**Preloaded Results Mechanism (lines 70-76):**\n- `SetPreloadedResults(results map[string]string)` configures engine to skip execution\n- Steps in the map are replayed with stored results instead of re-executing\n- Preserves wiring logic while skipping already-completed steps\n\n**Step Execution with Preload (lines 157-165):**\n- When a step has a preloaded result, engine immediately produces that result\n- Launches a goroutine that sends preloaded result to the results channel\n- This allows the engine to walk the workflow graph correctly while replaying previous steps\n\n### 5. **Agent Runner** (`/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`)\n\n**Resume Mode Handling (lines 93-99):**\n- When `ResumeFromStep` is set, calls `loadCompletedStepResults()`\n- Configures engine with preloaded results\n- Also resets `.cloche/output` only when NOT resuming (line 68)\n\n**loadCompletedStepResults() (lines 222-283):**\n- Reads `history.log` to extract step:result pairs\n- Walks workflow graph from entry step, collecting results until reaching resumeFrom step\n- Returns map of step_name -> result for steps before the resume point\n- Uses recursive walk to follow wires through the workflow graph\n\n**Resume Conversation Flag (lines 164-168):**\n- When resuming a prompt step, sets `ResumeConversation = true`\n- This flag is passed to the prompt adapter to use Claude Code's `-c` flag (resume conversation)\n\n### 6. **Host Runner** (`/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`)\n\n**ResumeRun() Method (lines 175-285):**\n- Takes a `domain.Run` and `resumeFrom` step name\n- Validates resume step exists in workflow\n- Resets run state: `RunStateRunning`, clears `ErrorMessage`, `CompletedAt`, `ActiveSteps`\n- Builds preloaded results using `buildPreloadedResults()`\n- Configures executor with `ResumeStep` field for prompt resume\n\n**buildPreloadedResults() (lines 290-327):**\n- Extracts step results from run's `StepExecutions`\n- Walks workflow graph to collect completed steps before resume point\n- Returns preloaded map for engine configuration\n\n**Host Workflow Resume Behavior:**\n- Persists run state changes back to store\n- Preserves log writer for full.log\n- Uses same engine/executor pattern as initial run\n\n### 7. **Host Executor** (`/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`)\n\n**ResumeStep Field (line 64):**\n- Stores the name of the step being resumed\n- Used in `executeAgent()` to enable conversation resume (lines 246-249)\n\n**Agent Resume Handling (lines 225-283):**\n- For prompt steps: sets `adapter.ResumeConversation = true` if matching resume step\n- For other steps: no special handling (scripts/workflows re-execute fresh)\n\n### 8. **gRPC Server** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n\n**RunWorkflow RPC with Resume (lines 90-94):**\n- Checks for resume mode via `resumeRunIDFromContext(ctx)` (lines 173-184)\n- If resume metadata present, calls `s.resumeRun()` instead of creating new run\n\n**resumeRun() Method (lines 199-222):**\n- Fetches run from store\n- Validates run is in failed state\n- Determines resume step: uses provided name or finds first failed step\n- Dispatches to either `resumeHostRun()` or `resumeContainerRun()` based on `run.IsHost`\n\n**resumeHostRun() (lines 224-238):**\n- Creates host runner with same configuration as normal host runs\n- Calls `runner.ResumeRun()` in a background goroutine\n- Returns immediately with run ID\n\n**resumeContainerRun() (lines 241-285):**\n- Verifies container still exists using `Inspect()`\n- Checks container is not still running\n- Commits container to create image preserving filesystem state\n- Starts new container from committed image with `--resume-from` flag\n- Calls `launchResumeContainer()` to track the resumed run\n\n**launchResumeContainer() (lines 287-315):**\n- Starts container with resume command: `[\"cloche-agent\", \".cloche/<workflow>.cloche\", \"--resume-from\", <step>]`\n- Tracks container using standard `trackRun()` mechanism\n\n### 9. **Docker Runtime** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`)\n\n**Commit() Method (lines 257-271):**\n- Creates Docker image from stopped container: `docker commit <containerID> cloche-resume-<short-id>`\n- Preserves all filesystem changes from failed run\n- Used only in resume path for container workflows\n\n**Other Methods:**\n- `Start()`: creates and starts container with custom command\n- `Wait()`: waits for container exit code\n- `Inspect()`: checks container running state\n- `CopyFrom()`/`Logs()`: extracts output after container stops\n\n### 10. **Prompt Adapter** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`)\n\n**Resume Conversation Flag (line 30):**\n- `ResumeConversation bool` field on Adapter struct\n\n**tryCommand() with Resume (lines 156-160):**\n- When `ResumeConversation` is true, adds `-c` flag to agent command\n- `-c` flag tells Claude Code to resume previous conversation instead of starting new one\n- Prompt becomes just \"retry\" instead of full assembly\n\n**assemblePrompt() (lines 372-410):**\n- When NOT resuming: assembles full prompt from template + user request + feedback\n- Result selection instructions added\n- This is skipped in resume mode (just \"retry\")\n\n### 11. **Agent Main** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`)\n\n**Resume Command Parsing (lines 29-35):**\n- Parses `--resume-from <step>` flag from command line\n- Passes to `RunnerConfig.ResumeFromStep`\n\n**Execution (lines 50-61):**\n- Creates runner with resume configuration\n- Calls `runner.Run()` which orchestrates resume logic\n\n---\n\n## Key Implementation Insights\n\n**Resume Flow for Container Workflows:**\n1. Client sends `cloche resume <run-id> [step-name]` with metadata headers\n2. Server finds run, validates it's failed\n3. Commits container to preserve filesystem\n4. Starts new container from committed image with `--resume-from` flag\n5. Agent runner loads completed step results from history\n6. Engine skips preloaded steps but replays wiring\n7. Resume step gets special handling (prompt conversation resume)\n\n**Resume Flow for Host Workflows:**\n1. Client sends resume with metadata (same as container)\n2. Server calls `runner.ResumeRun()` in background\n3. Runner resets run state to running\n4. Runner builds preloaded results from step executions\n5. Engine configured with preloaded results\n6. Resume step gets conversation resume if it's a prompt step\n\n**Step-Specific Resume Behavior:**\n- **Script/Workflow steps**: Re-execute fresh (no replay of previous output)\n- **Prompt steps**: Resume conversation with `-c` flag (continue previous conversation)\n- **Host workflow steps**: Same as container-side behavior\n\n**Critical State Management:**\n- Preloaded results prevent re-execution but preserve wiring\n- History log maintains step:result pairs for graph walkthrough\n- Container commit preserves filesystem state (workspace, git branches, outputs)\n- Run state transitions: Failed → Running → Terminal (Succeeded/Failed)\n\nAll files are located at the absolute paths provided above. The implementation is sophisticated, handling both container and host workflows with proper state management and step-specific resumption logic."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aaa26613755e99c26 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 81407\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 32645</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"4dd4f8e6-ae46-4d16-a94c-348313717d42","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand the resume command implementation. I need to understand:\n\n1. The current CLI command structure in cmd/cloche/ (especially main.go and help.go)\n2. The gRPC proto definition in api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto\n3. The domain types in internal/domain/run.go\n4. The engine in internal/engine/engine.go\n5. The agent runner in internal/agent/runner.go\n6. The host runner in internal/host/runner.go and internal/host/executor.go\n7. The gRPC server in internal/adapters/grpc/server.go\n8. The container runtime in internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go\n9. The prompt adapter in internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go\n10. The container ports in internal/ports/container.go\n11. The cmd/cloche-agent/main.go\n\nRead ALL of these files completely. Be very thorough - read every line of each file.","agentId":"aaa26613755e99c26","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the resume command implementation. Let me compile my findings into a comprehensive report.\n\n## Resume Command Implementation Analysis\n\nI have thoroughly explored the codebase and understand the complete resume command implementation. Here's a detailed breakdown:\n\n### 1. **CLI Command Structure** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`)\n\n**Resume Command Entry Point (lines 233-258):**\n- `cmdResume()` function parses arguments: `cloche resume <run-id> [step-name]`\n- Uses gRPC metadata headers to communicate resume intent:\n  - `x-cloche-resume-run-id`: the run ID to resume\n  - `x-cloche-resume-step`: optional step name to resume from\n- Calls `client.RunWorkflow()` with an empty `RunWorkflowRequest` (resume happens via metadata, not request fields)\n\n**Help Text** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go`, lines 87-115):\n- Detailed help describing resume behavior for different step types (script, prompt, workflow)\n- Prerequisites: workflow must be in failed state, container must exist for container workflows\n- Examples provided\n\n### 2. **gRPC Proto Definition** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`)\n\n**Key Details (lines 24-28):**\n- Resume mode is handled via gRPC metadata on the `RunWorkflow` RPC (not a separate RPC)\n- No dedicated `ResumeRun` RPC; uses metadata headers instead\n- Server extracts metadata and decides whether to resume or create new run\n\n### 3. **Domain Types** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`)\n\n**Run State Management:**\n- Run states: `pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n- `StepExecution` struct tracks: step name, result, startedAt, completedAt, logs, gitRef\n- `FindFirstFailedStep()` method (lines 127-134) finds the first failed step for auto-resume\n\n**Run Fields Relevant to Resume:**\n- `State`: must be `RunStateFailed` to resume\n- `StepExecutions`: contains history of all step executions with results\n- `ContainerID`: needed for container workflow resume (must still exist)\n- `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`: needed to find workflow definition\n\n### 4. **Engine** (`/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`)\n\n**Preloaded Results Mechanism (lines 70-76):**\n- `SetPreloadedResults(results map[string]string)` configures engine to skip execution\n- Steps in the map are replayed with stored results instead of re-executing\n- Preserves wiring logic while skipping already-completed steps\n\n**Step Execution with Preload (lines 157-165):**\n- When a step has a preloaded result, engine immediately produces that result\n- Launches a goroutine that sends preloaded result to the results channel\n- This allows the engine to walk the workflow graph correctly while replaying previous steps\n\n### 5. **Agent Runner** (`/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`)\n\n**Resume Mode Handling (lines 93-99):**\n- When `ResumeFromStep` is set, calls `loadCompletedStepResults()`\n- Configures engine with preloaded results\n- Also resets `.cloche/output` only when NOT resuming (line 68)\n\n**loadCompletedStepResults() (lines 222-283):**\n- Reads `history.log` to extract step:result pairs\n- Walks workflow graph from entry step, collecting results until reaching resumeFrom step\n- Returns map of step_name -> result for steps before