n- Dispatches to either `resumeHostRun()` or `resumeContainerRun()` based on `run.IsHost`\n\n**resumeHostRun() (lines 224-238):**\n- Creates host runner with same configuration as normal host runs\n- Calls `runner.ResumeRun()` in a background goroutine\n- Returns immediately with run ID\n\n**resumeContainerRun() (lines 241-285):**\n- Verifies container still exists using `Inspect()`\n- Checks container is not still running\n- Commits container to create image preserving filesystem state\n- Starts new container from committed image with `--resume-from` flag\n- Calls `launchResumeContainer()` to track the resumed run\n\n**launchResumeContainer() (lines 287-315):**\n- Starts container with resume command: `[\"cloche-agent\", \".cloche/<workflow>.cloche\", \"--resume-from\", <step>]`\n- Tracks container using standard `trackRun()` mechanism\n\n### 9. **Docker Runtime** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`)\n\n**Commit() Method (lines 257-271):**\n- Creates Docker image from stopped container: `docker commit <containerID> cloche-resume-<short-id>`\n- Preserves all filesystem changes from failed run\n- Used only in resume path for container workflows\n\n**Other Methods:**\n- `Start()`: creates and starts container with custom command\n- `Wait()`: waits for container exit code\n- `Inspect()`: checks container running state\n- `CopyFrom()`/`Logs()`: extracts output after container stops\n\n### 10. **Prompt Adapter** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`)\n\n**Resume Conversation Flag (line 30):**\n- `ResumeConversation bool` field on Adapter struct\n\n**tryCommand() with Resume (lines 156-160):**\n- When `ResumeConversation` is true, adds `-c` flag to agent command\n- `-c` flag tells Claude Code to resume previous conversation instead of starting new one\n- Prompt becomes just \"retry\" instead of full assembly\n\n**assemblePrompt() (lines 372-410):**\n- When NOT resuming: assembles full prompt from template + user request + feedback\n- Result selection instructions added\n- This is skipped in resume mode (just \"retry\")\n\n### 11. **Agent Main** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`)\n\n**Resume Command Parsing (lines 29-35):**\n- Parses `--resume-from <step>` flag from command line\n- Passes to `RunnerConfig.ResumeFromStep`\n\n**Execution (lines 50-61):**\n- Creates runner with resume configuration\n- Calls `runner.Run()` which orchestrates resume logic\n\n---\n\n## Key Implementation Insights\n\n**Resume Flow for Container Workflows:**\n1. Client sends `cloche resume <run-id> [step-name]` with metadata headers\n2. Server finds run, validates it's failed\n3. Commits container to preserve filesystem\n4. Starts new container from committed image with `--resume-from` flag\n5. Agent runner loads completed step results from history\n6. Engine skips preloaded steps but replays wiring\n7. Resume step gets special handling (prompt conversation resume)\n\n**Resume Flow for Host Workflows:**\n1. Client sends resume with metadata (same as container)\n2. Server calls `runner.ResumeRun()` in background\n3. Runner resets run state to running\n4. Runner builds preloaded results from step executions\n5. Engine configured with preloaded results\n6. Resume step gets conversation resume if it's a prompt step\n\n**Step-Specific Resume Behavior:**\n- **Script/Workflow steps**: Re-execute fresh (no replay of previous output)\n- **Prompt steps**: Resume conversation with `-c` flag (continue previous conversation)\n- **Host workflow steps**: Same as container-side behavior\n\n**Critical State Management:**\n- Preloaded results prevent re-execution but preserve wiring\n- History log maintains step:result pairs for graph walkthrough\n- Container commit preserves filesystem state (workspace, git branches, outputs)\n- Run state transitions: Failed → Running → Terminal (Succeeded/Failed)\n\nAll files are located at the absolute paths provided above. The implementation is sophisticated, handling both container and host workflows 