{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUnpJzSHuhmadkgcFGRrK6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of all the documentation I've read.\n\n## Documentation Summary\n\nI have thoroughly reviewed all documentation files in the `/workspace/docs/` directory. Here is a comprehensive overview:\n\n### Core Documentation Files\n\n#### 1. **docs/workflows.md**\nComprehensive DSL reference covering:\n- Workflow locations (container vs. host workflows)\n- Three-phase orchestration: `list-tasks`, `main`, `finalize`, and optional `release-task`\n- Step types: agent (prompt), script (run), workflow (host-only)\n- DSL syntax with examples\n- Wire output mappings for environment variable injection\n- Result protocol and marker system (`CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>`)\n- Execution model for both container and host workflows\n\n#### 2. **docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md**\nHigh-level architecture design documenting:\n- Three binaries: `cloche` (CLI), `cloched` (daemon), `cloche-agent` (in-container)\n- Communication patterns (gRPC CLI-to-daemon, JSON-lines agent-to-daemon)\n- Workflow DSL vocabulary and syntax\n- Hexagonal architecture (domain-independent core, ports/interfaces, adapters)\n- Container model with one-container-per-run and git-based result extraction\n- Capture system for step inputs/outputs/results\n- MVP scope and post-MVP features\n\n#### 3. **docs/USAGE.md**\nComplete CLI reference and usage guide including:\n- Core concepts and DSL syntax\n- Workflow configuration blocks (`container`, `host`)\n- File references with `file()` function\n- Wire output mappings with path expressions\n- Retry loops and parallel branches (fanout/collect)\n- Prompt assembly process\n- Agent command resolution and fallback chains\n- Agent setup guides for Claude Code and Codex\n- Host workflow three-phase model with environment variables\n- Complete CLI command reference: `init`, `run`, `status`, `list`, `logs`, `poll`, `stop`, `delete`, `health`, `workflow`, `validate`, `project`, `get`, `set`, `tasks`, `loop`, `shutdown`\n- Project layout specification\n- Daemon and client configuration\n- Dockerfile requirements\n\n#### 4. **docs/INSTALL.md**\nInstallation methods covering:\n- Build from source (Go 1.25+ required)\n- `go install` approach\n- Planned pre-built releases\n- Planned Homebrew installation\n- Verification steps\n- Upgrade instructions\n\n#### 5. **docs/SAFETY.md**\nSecurity best practices addressing:\n- The \"Lethal Trifecta\" (access to private data + untrusted input + external communication)\n- Minimizing host-side agent usage\n- Network allowlisting in containers\n- Filesystem isolation through copy-based model\n- Credential handling and authentication\n- Prompt hygiene and injection prevention\n- Code review before merging\n\n#### 6. **docs/agent-setup-claude.md**\nClaude Code setup guide:\n- Authentication via `~/.claude/` directory reuse\n- Dockerfile with Node.js and Claude Code npm install\n- Default agent configuration\n- Fallback chains for multiple agents\n- API key alternative approach\n\n#### 7. **docs/agent-setup-codex.md**\nCodex setup guide:\n- API key authentication via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`\n- Dockerfile requirements\n- Workflow configuration\n- Fallback chains\n\n### Design Documents\n\n#### 8. **docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md**\nResult protocol and fanout/collect design:\n- `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` stdout marker protocol\n- Exit code fallback convention\n- Multiple wires from same result (fanout)\n- Collect syntax (`all` and `any`) for joining parallel branches\n- Undeclared result validation\n- Domain model changes\n- Engine rewrite from linear to concurrent DAG walker\n\n#### 9. **docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md**\n12-task implementation plan:\n- Domain types for Collect (CollectMode, WireCondition)\n- NextSteps method for fanout support\n- Result extraction protocol in `internal/protocol/result.go`\n- Generic and prompt adapter updates for result markers\n- DSL parser collect syntax\n- Validation for collect conditions\n- Engine rewrite as DAG walker with concurrency\n- Run model changes from CurrentStep to ActiveSteps\n- Example workflow updates\n\n#### 10. **docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init-design.md**\nScaffold command design:\n- CLI interface: `cloche init [--workflow] [--image]`\n- Generated files structure\n- Template Dockerfile with multi-stage build\n- Prompt templates for implement and fix steps\n- Skip existing files behavior\n\n#### 11. **docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init.md**\nImplementation plan for init command:\n- `cmd/cloche/init.go` with template constants\n- Wire into `cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- Tests for default flags, custom flags, skip behavior\n- Manual verification steps\n\n#### 12. **docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-design.md** (partial read)\nThree-part redesign:\n- Directory layout change to `./cloche/` subdirectory\n- Daemon-side result extraction using `docker cp` instead of in-container git push\n- Git worktrees for concurrent extraction\n- `cloche poll` command for blocking on run completion\n\n#### 13. **docs/plans/2026-03-04-step-timeout-design.md**\nStep-level timeout feature:\n- Per-step `timeout = \"duration\"` DSL syntax\n- Engine changes with context deadlines\n- Config key validation for known vs. unknown keys\n- Timeout behavior routes to `fail` result\n\n#### 14. **docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md**\nMinimal base Docker image:\n- `debian:12-slim` base with git, ca-certificates, cloche-agent\n- Unprivileged `agent` user\n- `cloche-base:latest` and `cloche-base:<version>` tagging\n- Makefile changes for building base before project image\n- Simplifies project Dockerfiles\n\n#### 15. **docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md**\nProject evolution versioning:\n- `.cloche/version` file with integer counter\n- Incremented after evolution pipeline produces changes\n- Version display in web dashboard\n- Not gitignored (tracked in git history)\n\n#### 16. **docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md**\nHost workflow orchestration:\n- `.cloche/host.cloche` file for custom orchestration strategies\n- New `workflow` step type for dispatching container runs\n- `workflow_name` and `prompt_step` config keys\n- Step output capture to `.cloche/<run-id>/<step>.out`\n- Host workflow environment variables (CLOCHE_TASK_ID, CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR, etc.)\n\n#### 17. **docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md**\nProject settings file format:\n- Rename `.cloche/config` to `.cloche/config.toml`\n- TOML format with [orchestration] and [evolution] sections\n- Settings: concurrency, stagger_seconds, list_tasks_command, dedup_seconds, evolution parameters\n\n#### 18. **docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md**\nWire-level output mapping feature:\n- Syntax: `step-a:success -> step-b [ KEY = output.path ]`\n- Path expressions for JSON navigation\n- Examples with bd ready task integration\n- Validation for ambiguous key mappings\n- Interaction with CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT\n\n### Key Architectural Insights\n\n**Three-binary design:**\n- `cloche`: Short-lived CLI client\n- `cloched`: Long-running daemon managing container lifecycle\n- `cloche-agent`: Autonomous in-container executor\n\n**Workflow execution model:**\n- Container workflows: Linear or DAG with fanout/collect, run inside containers\n- Host workflows: Three-phase orchestration (list-tasks, main, finalize) running on host\n\n**Data flow:**\n- Prompts assembled from templates + user request + validation feedback\n- Results reported via stdout markers with exit-code fallback\n- Output mappings extract JSON fields to env vars\n- Container results extracted to git branches via daemon\n\n**Security model:**\n- Copy-based isolation (not bind mounts)\n- Network allowlisting in DSL (runtime enforcement pending)\n- Unprivileged agent user\n- Session-based agent authentication (Claude Code)\n- API key authentication (Codex)\n\n**Configuration:**\n- `.cloche/config.toml` for project settings\n- `.cloche/<workflow>.cloche` for workflow definitions\n- `.cloche/prompts/` for prompt templates\n- `.cloche/scripts/` for host-side scripts\n- `.cloche/overrides/` for files to apply on top of project in container\n\n### File Paths for Reference\n\nAll documentation files are in `/workspace/docs/`:\n- Main docs: `workflows.md`, `USAGE.md`, `INSTALL.md`, `SAFETY.md`\n- System design: `plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n- Agent guides: `agent-setup-claude.md`, `agent-setup-codex.md`\n- Design documents: Multiple `plans/` files with dates and feature-specific designs"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a690074d37fc43215 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 77137\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 42694</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1496100-58bb-4933-86a8-269a722f19f5","uuid":"9869b4b3-d0ed-493d-8df4-769c685f94c8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read all documentation files in the docs/ directory. Look for:\n1. docs/workflows.md\n2. docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md\n3. Any other .md files in docs/\n\nRead each file completely. Be very thorough.","agentId":"a690074d37fc43215","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of all the documentation I've read.\n\n## Documentation Summary\n\nI have thoroughly reviewed all documentation files in the `/workspace/docs/` directory. Here is a comprehensive overview:\n\n### Core Documentation Files\n\n#### 1. **docs/workflows.md**\nComprehensive DSL reference covering:\n- Workflow locations (container vs. host workflows)\n- Three-phase orchestration: `list-tasks`, `main`, `finalize`, and optional `release-task`\n- Step types: agent (prompt), script (run), workflow (host-only)\n- DSL syntax with examples\n- Wire output mappings for environment variable injection\n- Result protocol and